var book = {
	"name": "1 Kings",
	"numChapters": 22,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>Now King David was old, advanced in age; and they covered him with clothes, but he could not keep warm.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So his servants said to him, “Let them seek a young virgin for my lord the king, and let her attend the king and become his nurse; and let her lie in your bosom, that my lord the king may keep warm.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So they searched for a beautiful girl throughout all the territory of Israel, and found Abishag the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8721A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8721A\"></sup>Shunammite, and brought her to the king.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The girl was very beautiful; and she became the king’s nurse and served him, but the king did not cohabit with her.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8723B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8723B\"></sup>Adonijah the son of Haggith exalted himself, saying, “I will be king.” So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8723C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8723C\"></sup>he prepared for himself chariots and horsemen with fifty men to run before him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>His father had never crossed him at any time by asking, “Why have you done so?” And he was also a very handsome man, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8724D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8724D\"></sup>he was born after Absalom.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He had conferred with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8725E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8725E\"></sup>Joab the son of Zeruiah and with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8725F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8725F\"></sup>Abiathar the priest; and following <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8725G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8725G\"></sup>Adonijah they helped him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8726H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8726H\"></sup>Zadok the priest, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8726I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8726I\"></sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8726J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8726J\"></sup>Nathan the prophet, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8726K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8726K\"></sup>Shimei, Rei, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8726L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8726L\"></sup>the mighty men who belonged to David, were not with Adonijah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Adonijah sacrificed sheep and oxen and fatlings by the stone of Zoheleth, which is beside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8727M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8727M\"></sup>En-rogel; and he invited all his brothers, the king’s sons, and all the men of Judah, the king’s servants.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But he did not invite Nathan the prophet, Benaiah, the mighty men, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8728N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8728N\"></sup>Solomon his brother.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Nathan spoke to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8729O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8729O\"></sup>Bathsheba the mother of Solomon, saying, “Have you not heard that Adonijah the son of Haggith has become king, and David our lord does not know <i>it</i>?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So now come, please let me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8730P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8730P\"></sup>give you counsel and save your life and the life of your son Solomon.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Go at once to King David and say to him, ‘Have you not, my lord, O king, sworn to your maidservant, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8731Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8731Q\"></sup>Surely Solomon your son shall be king after me, and he shall sit on my throne”? Why then has Adonijah become king?’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Behold, while you are still there speaking with the king, I will come in after you and confirm your words.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Bathsheba went in to the king in the bedroom. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8733R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8733R\"></sup>the king was very old, and Abishag the Shunammite was ministering to the king.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Bathsheba bowed and prostrated herself before the king. And the king said, “What do you wish?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>She said to him, “My lord, you swore to your maidservant by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <i>saying</i>, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8735S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8735S\"></sup>Surely your son Solomon shall be king after me and he shall sit on my throne.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now, behold, Adonijah is king; and now, my lord the king, you do not know <i>it</i>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8737T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8737T\"></sup>He has sacrificed oxen and fatlings and sheep in abundance, and has invited all the sons of the king and Abiathar the priest and Joab the commander of the army, but he has not invited Solomon your servant.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for you now, my lord the king, the eyes of all Israel are on you, to tell them who shall sit on the throne of my lord the king after him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Otherwise it will come about, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8739U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8739U\"></sup>as soon as my lord the king sleeps with his fathers, that I and my son Solomon will be considered offenders.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Behold, while she was still speaking with the king, Nathan the prophet came in.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They told the king, saying, “Here is Nathan the prophet.” And when he came in before the king, he prostrated himself before the king with his face to the ground.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Nathan said, “My lord the king, have you said, ‘Adonijah shall be king after me, and he shall sit on my throne’?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8743V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8743V\"></sup>For he has gone down today and has sacrificed oxen and fatlings and sheep in abundance, and has invited all the king’s sons and the commanders of the army and Abiathar the priest, and behold, they are eating and drinking before him; and they say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8743W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8743W\"></sup><i>Long</i> live King Adonijah!’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8744X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8744X\"></sup>But me, <i>even</i> me your servant, and Zadok the priest and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada and your servant Solomon, he has not invited.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Has this thing been done by my lord the king, and you have not shown to your servants who should sit on the throne of my lord the king after him?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then King David said, “Call Bathsheba to me.” And she came into the king’s presence and stood before the king.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The king vowed and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8747Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8747Y\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, who has redeemed my life from all distress,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>surely as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8748Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8748Z\"></sup>I vowed to you by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the God of Israel, saying, ‘Your son Solomon shall be king after me, and he shall sit on my throne in my place’; I will indeed do so this day.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Bathsheba bowed with her face to the ground, and prostrated herself before the king and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8749AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8749AA\"></sup>May my lord King David live forever.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then King David said, “Call to me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8750AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8750AB\"></sup>Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada.” And they came into the king’s presence.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The king said to them, “Take with you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8751AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8751AC\"></sup>the servants of your lord, and have my son Solomon ride on my own mule, and bring him down to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8751AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8751AD\"></sup>Gihon.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Let Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8752AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8752AE\"></sup>anoint him there as king over Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8752AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8752AF\"></sup>blow the trumpet and say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8752AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8752AG\"></sup><i>Long</i> live King Solomon!’",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then you shall come up after him, and he shall come and sit on my throne and be king in my place; for I have appointed him to be ruler over Israel and Judah.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada answered the king and said, “Amen! Thus may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of my lord the king, say.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8755AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8755AH\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has been with my lord the king, so may He be with Solomon, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8755AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8755AI\"></sup>make his throne greater than the throne of my lord King David!”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8756AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8756AJ\"></sup>Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8756AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8756AK\"></sup>the Cherethites, and the Pelethites went down and had Solomon ride on King David’s mule, and brought him to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8756AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8756AL\"></sup>Gihon.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Zadok the priest then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8757AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8757AM\"></sup>took the horn of oil from the tent and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8757AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8757AN\"></sup>anointed Solomon. Then they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8757AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8757AO\"></sup>blew the trumpet, and all the people said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8757AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8757AP\"></sup><i>Long</i> live King Solomon!”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>All the people went up after him, and the people were playing on flutes and rejoicing with great joy, so that the earth shook at their noise.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Now Adonijah and all the guests who <i>were</i> with him heard <i>it</i> as they finished eating. When Joab heard the sound of the trumpet, he said, “Why is the city making such an uproar?”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>While he was still speaking, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8760AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8760AQ\"></sup>Jonathan the son of Abiathar the priest came. Then Adonijah said, “Come in, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8760AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8760AR\"></sup>you are a valiant man and bring good news.”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>But Jonathan replied to Adonijah, “No! Our lord King David has made Solomon king.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The king has also sent with him Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the Cherethites, and the Pelethites; and they have made him ride on the king’s mule.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet have anointed him king in Gihon, and they have come up from there rejoicing, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8763AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8763AS\"></sup>so that the city is in an uproar. This is the noise which you have heard.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Besides, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8764AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8764AT\"></sup>Solomon has even taken his seat on the throne of the kingdom.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Moreover, the king’s servants came to bless our lord King David, saying, ‘May <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8765AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8765AU\"></sup>your God make the name of Solomon better than your name and his throne greater than your throne!’ And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8765AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8765AV\"></sup>the king bowed himself on the bed.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>The king has also said thus, ‘Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8766AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8766AW\"></sup>has granted one to sit on my throne today while my own eyes see <i>it</i>.’”",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Then all the guests of Adonijah were terrified; and they arose and each went on his way.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And Adonijah was afraid of Solomon, and he arose, went and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8768AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8768AX\"></sup>took hold of the horns of the altar.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Now it was told Solomon, saying, “Behold, Adonijah is afraid of King Solomon, for behold, he has taken hold of the horns of the altar, saying, ‘Let King Solomon swear to me today that he will not put his servant to death with the sword.’”",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Solomon said, “If he is a worthy man, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8770AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8770AY\"></sup>not one of his hairs will fall to the ground; but if wickedness is found in him, he will die.”",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>So King Solomon sent, and they brought him down from the altar. And he came and prostrated himself before King Solomon, and Solomon said to him, “Go to your house.”"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>As David’s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8772A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8772A\"></sup>time to die drew near, he charged Solomon his son, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8773B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8773B\"></sup>I am going the way of all the earth. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8773C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8773C\"></sup>Be strong, therefore, and show yourself a man.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Keep the charge of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, to walk in His ways, to keep His statutes, His commandments, His ordinances, and His testimonies, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8774D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8774D\"></sup>according to what is written in the Law of Moses, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8774E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8774E\"></sup>you may succeed in all that you do and wherever you turn,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8775F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8775F\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may carry out His promise which He spoke concerning me, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8775G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8775G\"></sup>If your sons are careful of their way, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8775H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8775H\"></sup>to walk before Me in truth with all their heart and with all their soul, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8775I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8775I\"></sup>you shall not lack a man on the throne of Israel.’",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Now you also know what Joab the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8776J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8776J\"></sup>son of Zeruiah did to me, what he did to the two commanders of the armies of Israel, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8776K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8776K\"></sup>Abner the son of Ner, and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8776L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8776L\"></sup>Amasa the son of Jether, whom he killed; he also shed the blood of war in peace. And he put the blood of war on his belt about his waist, and on his sandals on his feet.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8777M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8777M\"></sup>So act according to your wisdom, and do not let his gray hair go down to Sheol in peace.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8778N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8778N\"></sup>show kindness to the sons of Barzillai the Gileadite, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8778O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8778O\"></sup>let them be among those who eat at your table; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8778P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8778P\"></sup>for they assisted me when I fled from Absalom your brother.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8779Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8779Q\"></sup>there is with you Shimei the son of Gera the Benjamite, of Bahurim; now it was he who cursed me with a violent curse on the day I went to Mahanaim. But when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8779R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8779R\"></sup>he came down to me at the Jordan, I swore to him by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, ‘I will not put you to death with the sword.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now therefore, do not let him go unpunished, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8780S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8780S\"></sup>for you are a wise man; and you will know what you ought to do to him, and you will bring his gray hair down to Sheol with blood.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8781T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8781T\"></sup>David slept with his fathers and was buried in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8781U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8781U\"></sup>the city of David.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8782V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8782V\"></sup>The days that David reigned over Israel <i>were</i> forty years: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8782W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8782W\"></sup>seven years he reigned in Hebron and thirty-three years he reigned in Jerusalem.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8783X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8783X\"></sup>Solomon sat on the throne of David his father, and his kingdom was firmly established.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now Adonijah the son of Haggith came to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon. And she said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8784Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8784Y\"></sup>Do you come peacefully?” And he said, “Peacefully.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he said, “I have something <i>to say</i> to you.” And she said, “Speak.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So he said, “You know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8786Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8786Z\"></sup>the kingdom was mine and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8786AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8786AA\"></sup>that all Israel expected me to be king; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8786AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8786AB\"></sup>however, the kingdom has turned about and become my brother’s, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8786AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8786AC\"></sup>for it was his from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now I am making one request of you; do not refuse me.” And she said to him, “Speak.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then he said, “Please speak to Solomon the king, for he will not refuse you, that he may give me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8788AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8788AD\"></sup>Abishag the Shunammite as a wife.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Bathsheba said, “Very well; I will speak to the king for you.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So Bathsheba went to King Solomon to speak to him for Adonijah. And the king arose to meet her, bowed before her, and sat on his throne; then he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8790AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8790AE\"></sup>had a throne set for the king’s mother, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8790AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8790AF\"></sup>she sat on his right.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then she said, “I am making one small request of you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8791AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8791AG\"></sup>do not refuse me.” And the king said to her, “Ask, my mother, for I will not refuse you.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So she said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8792AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8792AH\"></sup>Let Abishag the Shunammite be given to Adonijah your brother as a wife.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>King Solomon answered and said to his mother, “And why are you asking Abishag the Shunammite for Adonijah? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8793AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8793AI\"></sup>Ask for him also the kingdom—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8793AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8793AJ\"></sup>for he is my older brother—even for him, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8793AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8793AK\"></sup>Abiathar the priest, and for Joab the son of Zeruiah!”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then King Solomon swore by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “May God do so to me and more also, if Adonijah has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8794AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8794AL\"></sup>not spoken this word against his own life.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now therefore, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, who has established me and set me on the throne of David my father and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8795AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8795AM\"></sup>who has made me a house as He promised, surely Adonijah shall be put to death today.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So King Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8796AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8796AN\"></sup>sent Benaiah the son of Jehoiada; and he fell upon him so that he died.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then to Abiathar the priest the king said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8797AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8797AO\"></sup>Go to Anathoth to your own field, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8797AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8797AP\"></sup>for you deserve to die; but I will not put you to death at this time, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8797AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8797AQ\"></sup>you carried the ark of the Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span> before my father David, and because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8797AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8797AR\"></sup>you were afflicted in everything with which my father was afflicted.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So Solomon dismissed Abiathar from being priest to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in order to fulfill <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8798AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8798AS\"></sup>the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which He had spoken concerning the house of Eli in Shiloh.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now the news came to Joab, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8799AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8799AT\"></sup>for Joab had followed Adonijah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8799AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8799AU\"></sup>although he had not followed Absalom. And Joab fled to the tent of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8799AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8799AV\"></sup>took hold of the horns of the altar.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>It was told King Solomon that Joab had fled to the tent of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and behold, he is beside the altar. Then Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8800AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8800AW\"></sup>sent Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8800AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8800AX\"></sup>Go, fall upon him.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So Benaiah came to the tent of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said to him, “Thus the king has said, ‘Come out.’” But he said, “No, for I will die here.” And Benaiah brought the king word again, saying, “Thus spoke Joab, and thus he answered me.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The king said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8802AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8802AY\"></sup>Do as he has spoken and fall upon him and bury him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8802AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8802AZ\"></sup>that you may remove from me and from my father’s house the blood which Joab shed without cause.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8803BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8803BA\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will return his blood on his own head, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8803BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8803BB\"></sup>because he fell upon two men more righteous and better than he and killed them with the sword, while my father David did not know <i>it</i>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8803BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8803BC\"></sup>Abner the son of Ner, commander of the army of Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8803BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8803BD\"></sup>Amasa the son of Jether, commander of the army of Judah.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8804BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8804BE\"></sup>So shall their blood return on the head of Joab and on the head of his descendants forever; but to David and his descendants and his house and his throne, may there be peace from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forever.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8805BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8805BF\"></sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada went up and fell upon him and put him to death, and he was buried at his own house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8805BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8805BG\"></sup>in the wilderness.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8806BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8806BH\"></sup>The king appointed Benaiah the son of Jehoiada over the army in his place, and the king appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8806BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8806BI\"></sup>Zadok the priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8806BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8806BJ\"></sup>in the place of Abiathar.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Now the king sent and called for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8807BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8807BK\"></sup>Shimei and said to him, “Build for yourself a house in Jerusalem and live there, and do not go out from there to any place.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>For on the day you go out and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8808BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8808BL\"></sup>cross over the brook Kidron, you will know for certain that you shall surely die; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8808BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8808BM\"></sup>your blood shall be on your own head.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Shimei then said to the king, “The word is good. As my lord the king has said, so your servant will do.” So Shimei lived in Jerusalem many days.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>But it came about at the end of three years, that two of the servants of Shimei ran away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8810BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8810BN\"></sup>to Achish son of Maacah, king of Gath. And they told Shimei, saying, “Behold, your servants are in Gath.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Then Shimei arose and saddled his donkey, and went to Gath to Achish to look for his servants. And Shimei went and brought his servants from Gath.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>It was told Solomon that Shimei had gone from Jerusalem to Gath, and had returned.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>So the king sent and called for Shimei and said to him, “Did I not make you swear by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and solemnly warn you, saying, ‘You will know for certain that on the day you depart and go anywhere, you shall surely die’? And you said to me, ‘The word which I have heard is good.’",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Why then have you not kept the oath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the command which I have laid on you?”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The king also said to Shimei, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8815BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8815BO\"></sup>You know all the evil which you acknowledge in your heart, which you did to my father David; therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8815BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8815BP\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall return your evil on your own head.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But King Solomon shall be blessed, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8816BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8816BQ\"></sup>the throne of David shall be established before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forever.”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8817BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8817BR\"></sup>So the king commanded Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and he went out and fell upon him so that he died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8817BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8817BS\"></sup>Thus the kingdom was established in the hands of Solomon."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8818A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8818A\"></sup>Solomon formed a marriage alliance with Pharaoh king of Egypt, and took Pharaoh’s daughter <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8818B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8818B\"></sup>and brought her to the city of David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8818C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8818C\"></sup>until he had finished building his own house and the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8818D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8818D\"></sup>the wall around Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8819E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8819E\"></sup>The people were still sacrificing on the high places, because there was no house built for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> until those days.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8820F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8820F\"></sup>Solomon loved the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8820G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8820G\"></sup>walking in the statutes of his father David, except he sacrificed and burned incense on the high places.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8821H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8821H\"></sup>The king went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8821I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8821I\"></sup>Gibeon to sacrifice there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8821J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8821J\"></sup>for that was the great high place; Solomon offered a thousand burnt offerings on that altar.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8822K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8822K\"></sup>In Gibeon the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8822L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8822L\"></sup>in a dream at night; and God said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8822M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8822M\"></sup>Ask what <i>you wish</i> Me to give you.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Solomon said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8823N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8823N\"></sup>You have shown great lovingkindness to Your servant David my father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8823O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8823O\"></sup>according as he walked before You in truth and righteousness and uprightness of heart toward You; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8823P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8823P\"></sup>You have reserved for him this great lovingkindness, that You have given him a son to sit on his throne, as <i>it is</i> this day.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8824Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8824Q\"></sup>You have made Your servant king in place of my father David, yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8824R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8824R\"></sup>I am but a little child; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8824S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8824S\"></sup>I do not know how to go out or come in.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8825T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8825T\"></sup>Your servant is in the midst of Your people which You have chosen, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8825U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8825U\"></sup>a great people who are too many to be numbered or counted.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8826V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8826V\"></sup>give Your servant an understanding heart to judge Your people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8826W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8826W\"></sup>to discern between good and evil. For who is able to judge this great people of Yours?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>It was pleasing in the sight of the Lord that Solomon had asked this thing.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>God said to him, “Because you have asked this thing and have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8828X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8828X\"></sup>not asked for yourself long life, nor have asked riches for yourself, nor have you asked for the life of your enemies, but have asked for yourself discernment to understand justice,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8829Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8829Y\"></sup>I have done according to your words. Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8829Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8829Z\"></sup>I have given you a wise and discerning heart, so that there has been no one like you before you, nor shall one like you arise after you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8830AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8830AA\"></sup>I have also given you what you have not asked, both <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8830AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8830AB\"></sup>riches and honor, so that there will not be any among the kings like you all your days.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8831AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8831AC\"></sup>If you walk in My ways, keeping My statutes and commandments, as your father David walked, then I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8831AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8831AD\"></sup>prolong your days.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8832AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8832AE\"></sup>Solomon awoke, and behold, it was a dream. And he came to Jerusalem and stood before the ark of the covenant of the Lord, and offered burnt offerings and made peace offerings, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8832AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8832AF\"></sup>made a feast for all his servants.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then two women who were harlots came to the king and stood before him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The one woman said, “Oh, my lord, this woman and I live in the same house; and I gave birth to a child while she <i>was</i> in the house.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>It happened on the third day after I gave birth, that this woman also gave birth to a child, and we were together. There was no stranger with us in the house, only the two of us in the house.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>This woman’s son died in the night, because she lay on it.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So she arose in the middle of the night and took my son from beside me while your maidservant slept, and laid him in her bosom, and laid her dead son in my bosom.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When I rose in the morning to nurse my son, behold, he was dead; but when I looked at him carefully in the morning, behold, he was not my son, whom I had borne.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the other woman said, “No! For the living one is my son, and the dead one is your son.” But the first woman said, “No! For the dead one is your son, and the living one is my son.” Thus they spoke before the king.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then the king said, “The one says, ‘This is my son who is living, and your son is the dead one’; and the other says, ‘No! For your son is the dead one, and my son is the living one.’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The king said, “Get me a sword.” So they brought a sword before the king.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The king said, “Divide the living child in two, and give half to the one and half to the other.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the woman whose child <i>was</i> the living one spoke to the king, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8843AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8843AG\"></sup>she was deeply stirred over her son and said, “Oh, my lord, give her the living child, and by no means kill him.” But the other said, “He shall be neither mine nor yours; divide <i>him</i>!”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then the king said, “Give the first woman the living child, and by no means kill him. She is his mother.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When all Israel heard of the judgment which the king had handed down, they feared the king, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8845AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8845AH\"></sup>they saw that the wisdom of God was in him to administer justice."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Now King Solomon was king over all Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>These were his officials: Azariah the son of Zadok <i>was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8847A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8847A\"></sup>the priest;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Elihoreph and Ahijah, the sons of Shisha <i>were</i> secretaries; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8848B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8848B\"></sup>Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud <i>was</i> the recorder;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8849C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8849C\"></sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada <i>was</i> over the army; and Zadok and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8849D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8849D\"></sup>Abiathar <i>were</i> priests;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and Azariah the son of Nathan <i>was</i> over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8850E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8850E\"></sup>the deputies; and Zabud the son of Nathan, a priest, <i>was</i> the king’s friend;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and Ahishar was over the household; and Adoniram the son of Abda <i>was</i> over the men subject to forced labor.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Solomon had twelve deputies over all Israel, who provided for the king and his household; each man had to provide for a month in the year.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>These are their names: Ben-hur, in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8853F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8853F\"></sup>hill country of Ephraim;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Ben-deker in Makaz and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8854G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8854G\"></sup>Shaalbim and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8854H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8854H\"></sup>Beth-shemesh and Elonbeth-hanan;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Ben-hesed, in Arubboth (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8855I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8855I\"></sup>Socoh <i>was</i> his and all the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8855J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8855J\"></sup>Hepher);",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Ben-abinadab, <i>in</i> all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8856K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8856K\"></sup>height of Dor (Taphath the daughter of Solomon was his wife);",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Baana the son of Ahilud, <i>in</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8857L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8857L\"></sup>Taanach and Megiddo, and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8857M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8857M\"></sup>Beth-shean which is beside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8857N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8857N\"></sup>Zarethan below Jezreel, from Beth-shean to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8857O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8857O\"></sup>Abel-meholah as far as the other side of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8857P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8857P\"></sup>Jokmeam;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Ben-geber, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8858Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8858Q\"></sup>Ramoth-gilead (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8858R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8858R\"></sup>the towns of Jair, the son of Manasseh, which are in Gilead were his: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8858S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8858S\"></sup>the region of Argob, which is in Bashan, sixty great cities with walls and bronze bars <i>were</i> his);",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Ahinadab the son of Iddo, <i>in</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8859T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8859T\"></sup>Mahanaim;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8860U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8860U\"></sup>Ahimaaz, in Naphtali (he also married Basemath the daughter of Solomon);",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Baana the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8861V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8861V\"></sup>Hushai, in Asher and Bealoth;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jehoshaphat the son of Paruah, in Issachar;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8863W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8863W\"></sup>Shimei the son of Ela, in Benjamin;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Geber the son of Uri, in the land of Gilead, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8864X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8864X\"></sup>the country of Sihon king of the Amorites and of Og king of Bashan; and <i>he was</i> the only deputy who <i>was</i> in the land.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8865Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8865Y\"></sup>Judah and Israel <i>were</i> as numerous as the sand that is on the seashore in abundance; <i>they</i> were eating and drinking and rejoicing.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8866Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8866Z\"></sup>Now Solomon ruled over all the kingdoms <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8866AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8866AA\"></sup>from the River <i>to</i> the land of the Philistines and to the border of Egypt; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8866AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8866AB\"></sup><i>they</i> brought tribute and served Solomon all the days of his life.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Solomon’s provision for one day was thirty kors of fine flour and sixty kors of meal,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>ten fat oxen, twenty pasture-fed oxen, a hundred sheep besides deer, gazelles, roebucks, and fattened fowl.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For he had dominion over everything west of the River, from Tiphsah even to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8869AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8869AC\"></sup>Gaza, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8869AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8869AD\"></sup>over all the kings west of the River; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8869AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8869AE\"></sup>he had peace on all sides around about him.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8870AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8870AF\"></sup>So Judah and Israel lived in safety, every man under his vine and his fig tree, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8870AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8870AG\"></sup>from Dan even to Beersheba, all the days of Solomon.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8871AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8871AH\"></sup>Solomon had 40,000 stalls of horses for his chariots, and 12,000 horsemen.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Those deputies provided for King Solomon and all who came to King Solomon’s table, each in his month; they left nothing lacking.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They also brought barley and straw for the horses and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8873AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8873AI\"></sup>swift steeds to the place where it should be, each according to his charge.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8874AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8874AJ\"></sup>God gave Solomon wisdom and very great discernment and breadth of mind, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8874AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8874AK\"></sup>like the sand that is on the seashore.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Solomon’s wisdom surpassed the wisdom of all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8875AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8875AL\"></sup>the sons of the east and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8875AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8875AM\"></sup>all the wisdom of Egypt.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8876AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8876AN\"></sup>he was wiser than all men, than <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8876AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8876AO\"></sup>Ethan the Ezrahite, Heman, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8876AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8876AP\"></sup>Calcol and Darda, the sons of Mahol; and his fame was <i>known</i> in all the surrounding nations.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8877AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8877AQ\"></sup>He also spoke 3,000 proverbs, and his songs were 1,005.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He spoke of trees, from the cedar that is in Lebanon even to the hyssop that grows on the wall; he spoke also of animals and birds and creeping things and fish.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8879AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8879AR\"></sup>came from all peoples to hear the wisdom of Solomon, from all the kings of the earth who had heard of his wisdom."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8880A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8880A\"></sup>Now Hiram king of Tyre sent his servants to Solomon, when he heard that they had anointed him king in place of his father, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8880B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8880B\"></sup>Hiram had always been a friend of David.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8881C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8881C\"></sup>Solomon sent <i>word</i> to Hiram, saying,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“You know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8882D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8882D\"></sup>David my father was unable to build a house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God because of the wars which surrounded him, until the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> put them under the soles of his feet.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8883E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8883E\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God has given me rest on every side; there is neither adversary nor misfortune.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8884F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8884F\"></sup>I intend to build a house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to David my father, saying, ‘Your son, whom I will set on your throne in your place, he will build the house for My name.’",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now therefore, command that they cut for me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8885G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8885G\"></sup>cedars from Lebanon, and my servants will be with your servants; and I will give you wages for your servants according to all that you say, for you know that there is no one among us who knows how to cut timber like the Sidonians.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When Hiram heard the words of Solomon, he rejoiced greatly and said, “Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> today, who has given to David a wise son over this great people.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Hiram sent <i>word</i> to Solomon, saying, “I have heard <i>the message</i> which you have sent me; I will do what you desire concerning the cedar and cypress timber.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>My servants will bring <i>them</i> down from Lebanon to the sea; and I will make them into rafts <i>to go</i> by sea <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8888H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8888H\"></sup>to the place where you direct me, and I will have them broken up there, and you shall carry <i>them</i> away. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8888I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8888I\"></sup>you shall accomplish my desire by giving food to my household.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So Hiram gave Solomon as much as he desired of the cedar and cypress timber.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8890J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8890J\"></sup>Solomon then gave Hiram 20,000 kors of wheat as food for his household, and twenty kors of beaten oil; thus Solomon would give Hiram year by year.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8891K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8891K\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave wisdom to Solomon, just as He promised him; and there was peace between Hiram and Solomon, and the two of them made a covenant.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8892L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8892L\"></sup>King Solomon levied forced laborers from all Israel; and the forced laborers numbered 30,000 men.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He sent them to Lebanon, 10,000 a month in relays; they were in Lebanon a month <i>and</i> two months at home. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8893M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8893M\"></sup>Adoniram <i>was</i> over the forced laborers.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8894N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8894N\"></sup>Solomon had 70,000 transporters, and 80,000 hewers <i>of stone</i> in the mountains,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8895O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8895O\"></sup>besides Solomon’s 3,300 chief deputies who <i>were</i> over the project <i>and</i> who ruled over the people who were doing the work.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8896P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8896P\"></sup>the king commanded, and they quarried great stones, costly stones, to lay the foundation of the house with cut stones.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Solomon’s builders and Hiram’s builders and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8897Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8897Q\"></sup>the Gebalites cut them, and prepared the timbers and the stones to build the house."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8898A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8898A\"></sup>Now it came about in the four hundred and eightieth year after the sons of Israel came out of the land of Egypt, in the fourth year of Solomon’s reign over Israel, in the month of Ziv which is the second month, that he began to build the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>As for the house which King Solomon built for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, its length <i>was</i> sixty cubits and its width twenty <i>cubits</i> and its height thirty cubits.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The porch in front of the nave of the house <i>was</i> twenty cubits in length, corresponding to the width of the house, <i>and</i> its depth along the front of the house <i>was</i> ten cubits.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Also for the house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8901B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8901B\"></sup>he made windows with <i>artistic</i> frames.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8902C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8902C\"></sup>Against the wall of the house he built stories encompassing the walls of the house around both the nave and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8902D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8902D\"></sup>inner sanctuary; thus he made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8902E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8902E\"></sup>side chambers all around.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The lowest story <i>was</i> five cubits wide, and the middle <i>was</i> six cubits wide, and the third <i>was</i> seven cubits wide; for on the outside he made offsets <i>in the wall</i> of the house all around in order that <i>the beams</i> would not be inserted in the walls of the house.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8904F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8904F\"></sup>The house, while it was being built, was built of stone prepared at the quarry, and there was neither hammer nor axe nor any iron tool heard in the house while it was being built.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The doorway for the lowest side chamber <i>was</i> on the right side of the house; and they would go up by winding stairs to the middle <i>story</i>, and from the middle to the third.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8906G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8906G\"></sup>he built the house and finished it; and he covered the house with beams and planks of cedar.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He also built the stories against the whole house, each five cubits high; and they were fastened to the house with timbers of cedar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Solomon saying,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<i>Concerning</i> this house which you are building, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8909H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8909H\"></sup>if you will walk in My statutes and execute My ordinances and keep all My commandments by walking in them, then I will carry out My word with you which I spoke to David your father.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8910I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8910I\"></sup>I will dwell among the sons of Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8910J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8910J\"></sup>will not forsake My people Israel.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8911K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8911K\"></sup>So Solomon built the house and finished it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8912L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8912L\"></sup>built the walls of the house on the inside with boards of cedar; from the floor of the house to the ceiling he overlaid <i>the walls</i> on the inside with wood, and he overlaid the floor of the house with boards of cypress.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8913M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8913M\"></sup>He built twenty cubits on the rear part of the house with boards of cedar from the floor to the ceiling; he built <i>them</i> for it on the inside as an inner sanctuary, <i>even</i> as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8913N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8913N\"></sup>the most holy place.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The house, that is, the nave in front of <i>the inner sanctuary</i>, was forty cubits <i>long</i>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>There was cedar on the house within, carved <i>in the shape</i> of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8915O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8915O\"></sup>gourds and open flowers; all was cedar, there was no stone seen.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then he prepared an inner sanctuary within the house in order to place there the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The inner sanctuary <i>was</i> twenty cubits in length, twenty cubits in width, and twenty cubits in height, and he overlaid it with pure gold. He also overlaid the altar with cedar.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So Solomon overlaid the inside of the house with pure gold. And he drew chains of gold across the front of the inner sanctuary, and he overlaid it with gold.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He overlaid the whole house with gold, until all the house was finished. Also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8919P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8919P\"></sup>the whole altar which was by the inner sanctuary he overlaid with gold.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8920Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8920Q\"></sup>Also in the inner sanctuary he made two cherubim of olive wood, each ten cubits high.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Five cubits <i>was</i> the one wing of the cherub and five cubits the other wing of the cherub; from the end of one wing to the end of the other wing <i>were</i> ten cubits.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The other cherub <i>was</i> ten cubits; both the cherubim were of the same measure and the same form.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The height of the one cherub <i>was</i> ten cubits, and so <i>was</i> the other cherub.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He placed the cherubim in the midst of the inner house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8924R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8924R\"></sup>the wings of the cherubim were spread out, so that the wing of the one was touching the <i>one</i> wall, and the wing of the other cherub was touching the other wall. So their wings were touching each other in the center of the house.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He also overlaid the cherubim with gold.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then he carved all the walls of the house round about with carved engravings of cherubim, palm trees, and open flowers, inner and outer <i>sanctuaries</i>.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He overlaid the floor of the house with gold, inner and outer <i>sanctuaries</i>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For the entrance of the inner sanctuary he made doors of olive wood, the lintel <i>and</i> five-sided doorposts.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So <i>he made</i> two doors of olive wood, and he carved on them carvings of cherubim, palm trees, and open flowers, and overlaid them with gold; and he spread the gold on the cherubim and on the palm trees.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So also he made for the entrance of the nave four-sided doorposts of olive wood",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8931S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8931S\"></sup>two doors of cypress wood; the two leaves of the one door turned on pivots, and the two leaves of the other door turned on pivots.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>He carved <i>on it</i> cherubim, palm trees, and open flowers; and he overlaid <i>them</i> with gold evenly applied on the engraved work.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8933T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8933T\"></sup>He built the inner court with three rows of cut stone and a row of cedar beams.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8934U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8934U\"></sup>In the fourth year the foundation of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was laid, in the month of Ziv.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>In the eleventh year, in the month of Bul, which is the eighth month, the house was finished throughout all its parts and according to all its plans. So he was seven years in building it."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8936A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8936A\"></sup>Solomon was building his own house thirteen years, and he finished all his house.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8937B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8937B\"></sup>He built the house of the forest of Lebanon; its length was 100 cubits and its width 50 cubits and its height 30 cubits, on four rows of cedar pillars with cedar beams on the pillars.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>It was paneled with cedar above the side chambers which were on the 45 pillars, 15 in each row.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><i>There were artistic window</i> frames in three rows, and window was opposite window in three ranks.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>All the doorways and doorposts <i>had</i> squared <i>artistic</i> frames, and window was opposite window in three ranks.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then he made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8941C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8941C\"></sup>the hall of pillars; its length was 50 cubits and its width 30 cubits, and a porch <i>was</i> in front of them and pillars and a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8941D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8941D\"></sup>threshold in front of them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He made the hall of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8942E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8942E\"></sup>throne where he was to judge, the hall of judgment, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8942F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8942F\"></sup>it was paneled with cedar from floor to floor.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>His house where he was to live, the other court inward from the hall, was of the same workmanship. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8943G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8943G\"></sup>He also made a house like this hall for Pharaoh’s daughter, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8943H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8943H\"></sup>whom Solomon had married.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>All these were of costly stones, of stone cut according to measure, sawed with saws, inside and outside; even from the foundation to the coping, and so on the outside to the great court.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The foundation was of costly stones, <i>even</i> large stones, stones of ten cubits and stones of eight cubits.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And above were costly stones, stone cut according to measure, and cedar.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8947I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8947I\"></sup>the great court all around <i>had</i> three rows of cut stone and a row of cedar beams even as the inner court of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8947J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8947J\"></sup>the porch of the house.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8948K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8948K\"></sup>King Solomon sent and brought Hiram from Tyre.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8949L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8949L\"></sup>He was a widow’s son from the tribe of Naphtali, and his father was a man of Tyre, a worker in bronze; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8949M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8949M\"></sup>he was filled with wisdom and understanding and skill for doing any work in bronze. So he came to King Solomon and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8949N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8949N\"></sup>performed all his work.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He fashioned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8950O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8950O\"></sup>the two pillars of bronze; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8950P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8950P\"></sup>eighteen cubits was the height of one pillar, and a line of twelve cubits measured the circumference of both.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He also made two capitals of molten bronze to set on the tops of the pillars; the height of the one capital was five cubits and the height of the other capital was five cubits.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><i>There were</i> nets of network and twisted threads of chainwork for the capitals which were on the top of the pillars; seven for the one capital and seven for the other capital.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So he made the pillars, and two rows around on the one network to cover the capitals which were on the top of the pomegranates; and so he did for the other capital.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The capitals which <i>were</i> on the top of the pillars in the porch were of lily design, four cubits.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><i>There were</i> capitals on the two pillars, even above <i>and</i> close to the rounded projection which was beside the network; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8955Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8955Q\"></sup>the pomegranates <i>numbered</i> two hundred in rows around both capitals.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8956R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8956R\"></sup>Thus he set up the pillars at the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8956S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8956S\"></sup>porch of the nave; and he set up the right pillar and named it Jachin, and he set up the left pillar and named it Boaz.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>On the top of the pillars was lily design. So the work of the pillars was finished.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8958T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8958T\"></sup>Now he made the sea of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8958U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8958U\"></sup>cast <i>metal</i> ten cubits from brim to brim, circular in form, and its height was five cubits, and thirty cubits in circumference.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Under its brim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8959V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8959V\"></sup>gourds went around encircling it ten to a cubit, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8959W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8959W\"></sup>completely surrounding the sea; the gourds were in two rows, cast with the rest.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8960X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8960X\"></sup>It stood on twelve oxen, three facing north, three facing west, three facing south, and three facing east; and the sea <i>was set</i> on top of them, and all their rear parts <i>turned</i> inward.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>It was a handbreadth thick, and its brim was made like the brim of a cup, <i>as</i> a lily blossom; it could hold two thousand baths.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8962Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8962Y\"></sup>he made the ten stands of bronze; the length of each stand was four cubits and its width four cubits and its height three cubits.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>This was the design of the stands: they had borders, even borders between the frames,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and on the borders which were between the frames <i>were</i> lions, oxen and cherubim; and on the frames there <i>was</i> a pedestal above, and beneath the lions and oxen <i>were</i> wreaths of hanging work.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now each stand had four bronze wheels with bronze axles, and its four feet had supports; beneath the basin <i>were</i> cast supports with wreaths at each side.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Its opening inside the crown at the top <i>was</i> a cubit, and its opening <i>was</i> round like the design of a pedestal, a cubit and a half; and also on its opening <i>there were</i> engravings, and their borders were square, not round.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The four wheels <i>were</i> underneath the borders, and the axles of the wheels <i>were</i> on the stand. And the height of a wheel <i>was</i> a cubit and a half.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The workmanship of the wheels <i>was</i> like the workmanship of a chariot wheel. Their axles, their rims, their spokes, and their hubs <i>were</i> all cast.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now <i>there were</i> four supports at the four corners of each stand; its supports <i>were</i> part of the stand itself.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>On the top of the stand <i>there was</i> a circular form half a cubit high, and on the top of the stand its stays and its borders <i>were</i> part of it.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>He engraved on the plates of its stays and on its borders, cherubim, lions and palm trees, according to the clear space on each, with wreaths <i>all</i> around.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8972Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8972Z\"></sup>He made the ten stands like this: all of them had one casting, one measure and one form.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8973AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8973AA\"></sup>He made ten basins of bronze, one basin held forty baths; each basin <i>was</i> four cubits, <i>and</i> on each of the ten stands <i>was</i> one basin.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Then he set the stands, five on the right side of the house and five on the left side of the house; and he set the sea <i>of cast metal</i> on the right side of the house eastward toward the south.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Now Hiram made the basins and the shovels and the bowls. So Hiram finished doing all the work which he performed for King Solomon <i>in</i> the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>:",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>the two pillars and the <i>two</i> bowls of the capitals which <i>were</i> on the top of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8976AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8976AB\"></sup>two pillars, and the two networks to cover the two bowls of the capitals which <i>were</i> on the top of the pillars;",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8977AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8977AC\"></sup>four hundred pomegranates for the two networks, two rows of pomegranates for each network to cover the two bowls of the capitals which <i>were</i> on the tops of the pillars;",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>and the ten stands with the ten basins on the stands;",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8979AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8979AD\"></sup>the one sea and the twelve oxen under the sea;",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8980AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8980AE\"></sup>the pails and the shovels and the bowls; even all these utensils which Hiram made for King Solomon <i>in</i> the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>were</i> of polished bronze.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8981AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8981AF\"></sup>In the plain of the Jordan the king cast them, in the clay ground between <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8981AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8981AG\"></sup>Succoth and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8981AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8981AH\"></sup>Zarethan.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Solomon left all the utensils <i>unweighed</i>, because <i>they were</i> too many; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8982AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8982AI\"></sup>the weight of the bronze could not be ascertained.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Solomon made all the furniture which <i>was in</i> the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8983AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8983AJ\"></sup>the golden altar and the golden table on which <i>was</i> the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8983AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8983AK\"></sup>bread of the Presence;",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>and the lampstands, five on the right side and five on the left, in front of the inner sanctuary, of pure gold; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8984AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8984AL\"></sup>the flowers and the lamps and the tongs, of gold;",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>and the cups and the snuffers and the bowls and the spoons and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8985AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8985AM\"></sup>firepans, of pure gold; and the hinges both for the doors of the inner house, the most holy place, <i>and</i> for the doors of the house, <i>that is</i>, of the nave, of gold.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8986AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8986AN\"></sup>Thus all the work that King Solomon performed <i>in</i> the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was finished. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8986AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8986AO\"></sup>Solomon brought in the things dedicated by his father David, the silver and the gold and the utensils, <i>and</i> he put them in the treasuries of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8987A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8987A\"></sup>Then Solomon assembled the elders of Israel and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8987B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8987B\"></sup>the heads of the tribes, the leaders of the fathers’ <i>households</i> of the sons of Israel, to King Solomon in Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8987C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8987C\"></sup>to bring up the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8987D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8987D\"></sup>the city of David, which is Zion.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>All the men of Israel assembled themselves to King Solomon at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8988E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8988E\"></sup>the feast, in the month Ethanim, which is the seventh month.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then all the elders of Israel came, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8989F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8989F\"></sup>the priests took up the ark.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They brought up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8990G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8990G\"></sup>the tent of meeting and all the holy utensils, which were in the tent, and the priests and the Levites brought them up.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And King Solomon and all the congregation of Israel, who were assembled to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8991H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8991H\"></sup>were with him before the ark, sacrificing so many sheep and oxen they could not be counted or numbered.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8992I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8992I\"></sup>the priests brought the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8992J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8992J\"></sup>to its place, into the inner sanctuary of the house, to the most holy place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8992K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8992K\"></sup>under the wings of the cherubim.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For the cherubim spread <i>their</i> wings over the place of the ark, and the cherubim made a covering over the ark and its poles from above.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8994L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8994L\"></sup>the poles were so long that the ends of the poles could be seen from the holy place before the inner sanctuary, but they could not be seen outside; they are there to this day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8995M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8995M\"></sup>There was nothing in the ark except the two tablets of stone which Moses put there at Horeb, where <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8995N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8995N\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made a covenant with the sons of Israel, when they came out of the land of Egypt.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>It happened that when the priests came from the holy place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8996O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8996O\"></sup>the cloud filled the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>so that the priests could not stand to minister because of the cloud, for the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8998P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8998P\"></sup>Then Solomon said,“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8998Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8998Q\"></sup>He would dwell in the thick cloud.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8999R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8999R\"></sup>I have surely built You a lofty house,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8999S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8999S\"></sup>A place for Your dwelling forever.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the king faced about and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9000T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9000T\"></sup>blessed all the assembly of Israel, while all the assembly of Israel was standing.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9001U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9001U\"></sup>Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9001V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9001V\"></sup>who spoke with His mouth to my father David and has fulfilled <i>it</i> with His hand, saying,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9002W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9002W\"></sup>Since the day that I brought My people Israel from Egypt, I did not choose a city out of all the tribes of Israel <i>in which</i> to build a house that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9002X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9002X\"></sup>My name might be there, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9002Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9002Y\"></sup>I chose David to be over My people Israel.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9003Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9003Z\"></sup>Now it was in the heart of my father David to build a house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to my father David, ‘Because it was in your heart to build a house for My name, you did well that it was in your heart.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9005AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9005AA\"></sup>Nevertheless you shall not build the house, but your son who will be born to you, he will build the house for My name.’",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has fulfilled His word which He spoke; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9006AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9006AB\"></sup>I have risen in place of my father David and sit on the throne of Israel, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> promised, and have built the house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>There I have set a place for the ark, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9007AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9007AC\"></sup>in which is the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which He made with our fathers when He brought them from the land of Egypt.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9008AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9008AD\"></sup>Solomon stood before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the presence of all the assembly of Israel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9008AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9008AE\"></sup>spread out his hands toward heaven.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9009AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9009AF\"></sup>there is no God like You in heaven above or on earth beneath, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9009AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9009AG\"></sup>keeping covenant and <i>showing</i> lovingkindness to Your servants who walk before You with all their heart,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>who have kept with Your servant, my father David, that which You have promised him; indeed, You have spoken with Your mouth and have fulfilled it with Your hand as it is this day.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now therefore, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, keep with Your servant David my father that which You have promised him, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9011AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9011AH\"></sup>You shall not lack a man to sit on the throne of Israel, if only your sons take heed to their way to walk before Me as you have walked.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now therefore, O God of Israel, let Your word, I pray, be confirmed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9012AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9012AI\"></sup>which You have spoken to Your servant, my father David.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“But will God indeed dwell on the earth? Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9013AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9013AJ\"></sup>heaven and the highest heaven cannot contain You, how much less this house which I have built!",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Yet have regard to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9014AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9014AK\"></sup>prayer of Your servant and to his supplication, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, to listen to the cry and to the prayer which Your servant prays before You today;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9015AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9015AL\"></sup>that Your eyes may be open toward this house night and day, toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9015AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9015AM\"></sup>the place of which You have said, ‘My name shall be there,’ to listen to the prayer which Your servant shall pray toward this place.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9016AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9016AN\"></sup>Listen to the supplication of Your servant and of Your people Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9016AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9016AO\"></sup>when they pray toward this place; hear in heaven Your dwelling place; hear and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9016AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9016AP\"></sup>forgive.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9017AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9017AQ\"></sup>If a man sins against his neighbor and is made to take an oath, and he comes <i>and</i> takes an oath before Your altar in this house,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>then hear in heaven and act and judge Your servants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9018AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9018AR\"></sup>condemning the wicked by bringing his way on his own head and justifying the righteous by giving him according to his righteousness.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9019AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9019AS\"></sup>When Your people Israel are defeated before an enemy, because they have sinned against You, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9019AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9019AT\"></sup>if they turn to You again and confess Your name and pray and make supplication to You in this house,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>then hear in heaven, and forgive the sin of Your people Israel, and bring them back to the land which You gave to their fathers.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9021AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9021AU\"></sup>When the heavens are shut up and there is no rain, because they have sinned against You, and they pray toward this place and confess Your name and turn from their sin when You afflict them,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>then hear in heaven and forgive the sin of Your servants and of Your people Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9022AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9022AV\"></sup>indeed, teach them the good way in which they should walk. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9022AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9022AW\"></sup>send rain on Your land, which You have given Your people for an inheritance.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9023AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9023AX\"></sup>If there is famine in the land, if there is pestilence, if there is blight <i>or</i> mildew, locust <i>or</i> grasshopper, if their enemy besieges them in the land of their cities, whatever plague, whatever sickness <i>there is</i>,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>whatever prayer or supplication is made by any man <i>or</i> by all Your people Israel, each knowing the affliction of his own heart, and spreading his hands toward this house;",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>then hear in heaven Your dwelling place, and forgive and act and render to each according to all his ways, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9025AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9025AY\"></sup>whose heart You know, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9025AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9025AZ\"></sup>You alone know the hearts of all the sons of men,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>that they may fear You all the days that they live in the land which You have given to our fathers.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“Also concerning the foreigner who is not of Your people Israel, when he comes from a far country for Your name’s sake",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>(for they will hear of Your great name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9028BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9028BA\"></sup>and Your mighty hand, and of Your outstretched arm); when he comes and prays toward this house,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>hear in heaven Your dwelling place, and do according to all for which the foreigner calls to You, in order <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9029BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9029BB\"></sup>that all the peoples of the earth may know Your name, to fear You, as <i>do</i> Your people Israel, and that they may know that this house which I have built is called by Your name.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“When Your people go out to battle against their enemy, by whatever way You shall send them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9030BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9030BC\"></sup>they pray to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> toward the city which You have chosen and the house which I have built for Your name,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>then hear in heaven their prayer and their supplication, and maintain their cause.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“When they sin against You (for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9032BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9032BD\"></sup>there is no man who does not sin) and You are angry with them and deliver them to an enemy, so that they take them away captive <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9032BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9032BE\"></sup>to the land of the enemy, far off or near;",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9033BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9033BF\"></sup>if they take thought in the land where they have been taken captive, and repent and make supplication to You in the land of those who have taken them captive, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9033BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9033BG\"></sup>We have sinned and have committed iniquity, we have acted wickedly’;",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9034BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9034BH\"></sup>if they return to You with all their heart and with all their soul in the land of their enemies who have taken them captive, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9034BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9034BI\"></sup>pray to You toward their land which You have given to their fathers, the city which You have chosen, and the house which I have built for Your name;",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>then hear their prayer and their supplication in heaven Your dwelling place, and maintain their cause,",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>and forgive Your people who have sinned against You and all their transgressions which they have transgressed against You, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9036BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9036BJ\"></sup>make them <i>objects of</i> compassion before those who have taken them captive, that they may have compassion on them",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>(<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9037BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9037BK\"></sup>for they are Your people and Your inheritance which You have brought forth from Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9037BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9037BL\"></sup>from the midst of the iron furnace),",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9038BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9038BM\"></sup>that Your eyes may be open to the supplication of Your servant and to the supplication of Your people Israel, to listen to them whenever they call to You.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>For You have separated them from all the peoples of the earth as Your inheritance, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9039BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9039BN\"></sup>as You spoke through Moses Your servant, when You brought our fathers forth from Egypt, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>.”",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9040BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9040BO\"></sup>When Solomon had finished praying this entire prayer and supplication to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9040BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9040BP\"></sup>he arose from before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, from kneeling on his knees with his hands spread toward heaven.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>And he stood and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9041BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9041BQ\"></sup>blessed all the assembly of Israel with a loud voice, saying:",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>“Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who has given rest to His people Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9042BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9042BR\"></sup>according to all that He promised; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9042BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9042BS\"></sup>not one word has failed of all His good promise, which He promised through Moses His servant.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God be with us, as He was with our fathers; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9043BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9043BT\"></sup>may He not leave us or forsake us,",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9044BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9044BU\"></sup>He may incline our hearts to Himself, to walk in all His ways and to keep His commandments and His statutes and His ordinances, which He commanded our fathers.",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>And may these words of mine, with which I have made supplication before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, be near to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God day and night, that He may maintain the cause of His servant and the cause of His people Israel, as each day requires,",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9046BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9046BV\"></sup>that all the peoples of the earth may know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9046BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9046BW\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is God; there is no one else.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9047BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9047BX\"></sup>Let your heart therefore be wholly devoted to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, to walk in His statutes and to keep His commandments, as at this day.”",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9048BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9048BY\"></sup>Now the king and all Israel with him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9048BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9048BZ\"></sup>offered sacrifice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>Solomon offered for the sacrifice of peace offerings, which he offered to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, 22,000 oxen and 120,000 sheep. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9049CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9049CA\"></sup>So the king and all the sons of Israel dedicated the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>On the same day the king consecrated the middle of the court that <i>was</i> before the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because there he offered the burnt offering and the grain offering and the fat of the peace offerings; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9050CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9050CB\"></sup>the bronze altar that <i>was</i> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>was</i> too small to hold the burnt offering and the grain offering and the fat of the peace offerings.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9051CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9051CC\"></sup>Solomon observed the feast at that time, and all Israel with him, a great assembly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9051CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9051CD\"></sup>from the entrance of Hamath <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9051CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9051CE\"></sup>to the brook of Egypt, before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, for seven days and seven <i>more</i> days, <i>even</i> fourteen days.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>On the eighth day he sent the people away and they blessed the king. Then they went to their tents joyful and glad of heart for all the goodness that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had shown to David His servant and to Israel His people."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9053A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9053A\"></sup>Now it came about when Solomon had finished building the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9053B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9053B\"></sup>the king’s house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9053C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9053C\"></sup>all that Solomon desired to do,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9054D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9054D\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to Solomon a second time, as He had appeared to him at Gibeon.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9055E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9055E\"></sup>I have heard your prayer and your supplication, which you have made before Me; I have consecrated this house which you have built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9055F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9055F\"></sup>by putting My name there forever, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9055G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9055G\"></sup>My eyes and My heart will be there perpetually.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>As for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9056H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9056H\"></sup>if you will walk before Me as your father David walked, in integrity of heart and uprightness, doing according to all that I have commanded you <i>and</i> will keep My statutes and My ordinances,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9057I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9057I\"></sup>I will establish the throne of your kingdom over Israel forever, just as I promised to your father David, saying, ‘You shall not lack a man on the throne of Israel.’",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9058J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9058J\"></sup>But if you or your sons indeed turn away from following Me, and do not keep My commandments and My statutes which I have set before you, and go and serve other gods and worship them,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9059K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9059K\"></sup>then I will cut off Israel from the land which I have given them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9059L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9059L\"></sup>the house which I have consecrated for My name, I will cast out of My sight. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9059M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9059M\"></sup>Israel will become a proverb and a byword among all peoples.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And this house will become <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9060N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9060N\"></sup>a heap of ruins; everyone who passes by will be astonished and hiss and say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9060O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9060O\"></sup>Why has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> done thus to this land and to this house?’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And they will say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9061P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9061P\"></sup>Because they forsook the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, who brought their fathers out of the land of Egypt, and adopted other gods and worshiped them and served them, therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has brought all this adversity on them.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9062Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9062Q\"></sup>It came about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9062R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9062R\"></sup>at the end of twenty years in which Solomon had built the two houses, the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the king’s house",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>(Hiram king of Tyre had supplied Solomon with cedar and cypress timber and gold according to all his desire), then King Solomon gave Hiram twenty cities in the land of Galilee.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Hiram came out from Tyre to see the cities which Solomon had given him, and they did not please him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He said, “What are these cities which you have given me, my brother?” So they were called the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9065S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9065S\"></sup>Cabul to this day.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9066T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9066T\"></sup>And Hiram sent to the king 120 talents of gold.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now this is the account of the forced labor which King Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9067U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9067U\"></sup>levied to build the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, his own house, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9067V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9067V\"></sup>Millo, the wall of Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9067W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9067W\"></sup>Hazor, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9067X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9067X\"></sup>Megiddo, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9067Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9067Y\"></sup>Gezer.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><i>For</i> Pharaoh king of Egypt had gone up and captured Gezer and burned it with fire, and killed the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9068Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9068Z\"></sup>Canaanites who lived in the city, and had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9068AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9068AA\"></sup>given it <i>as</i> a dowry to his daughter, Solomon’s wife.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Solomon rebuilt Gezer and the lower <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9069AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9069AB\"></sup>Beth-horon",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9070AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9070AC\"></sup>Baalath and Tamar in the wilderness, in the land <i>of Judah</i>,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and all the storage cities which Solomon had, even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9071AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9071AD\"></sup>the cities for his chariots and the cities for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9071AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9071AE\"></sup>his horsemen, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9071AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9071AF\"></sup>all that it pleased Solomon to build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon, and in all the land under his rule.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><i>As for</i> all the people who were left of the Amorites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Hivites and the Jebusites, who were not of the sons of Israel,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9073AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9073AG\"></sup>their descendants who were left after them in the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9073AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9073AH\"></sup>whom the sons of Israel were unable to destroy utterly, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9073AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9073AI\"></sup>from them Solomon levied <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9073AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9073AJ\"></sup>forced laborers, even to this day.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9074AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9074AK\"></sup>did not make slaves of the sons of Israel; for they were men of war, his servants, his princes, his captains, his chariot commanders, and his horsemen.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>These <i>were</i> the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9075AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9075AL\"></sup>chief officers who <i>were</i> over Solomon’s work, five hundred and fifty, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9075AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9075AM\"></sup>who ruled over the people doing the work.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>As soon as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9076AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9076AN\"></sup>Pharaoh’s daughter came up from the city of David to her house which <i>Solomon</i> had built for her, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9076AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9076AO\"></sup>then he built the Millo.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9077AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9077AP\"></sup>three times in a year Solomon offered burnt offerings and peace offerings on the altar which he built to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, burning incense with them <i>on the altar</i> which <i>was</i> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. So he finished the house.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>King Solomon also built a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9078AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9078AQ\"></sup>fleet of ships in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9078AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9078AR\"></sup>Ezion-geber, which is near Eloth on the shore of the Red Sea, in the land of Edom.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9079AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9079AS\"></sup>And Hiram sent his servants with the fleet, sailors who knew the sea, along with the servants of Solomon.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9080AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9080AT\"></sup>Ophir and took four hundred and twenty talents of gold from there, and brought <i>it</i> to King Solomon."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9081A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9081A\"></sup>Now when the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9081B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9081B\"></sup>queen of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9081C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9081C\"></sup>Sheba heard about the fame of Solomon concerning the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, she came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9081D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9081D\"></sup>to test him with difficult questions.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So she came to Jerusalem with a very large retinue, with camels <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9082E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9082E\"></sup>carrying spices and very much gold and precious stones. When she came to Solomon, she spoke with him about all that was in her heart.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Solomon answered all her questions; nothing was hidden from the king which he did not explain to her.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the queen of Sheba perceived all the wisdom of Solomon, the house that he had built,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>the food of his table, the seating of his servants, the attendance of his waiters and their attire, his cupbearers, and his stairway by which he went up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, there was no more spirit in her.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then she said to the king, “It was a true report which I heard in my own land about your words and your wisdom.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nevertheless I did not believe the reports, until I came and my eyes had seen it. And behold, the half was not told me. You exceed <i>in</i> wisdom and prosperity the report which I heard.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>How <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9088F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9088F\"></sup>blessed are your men, how blessed are these your servants who stand before you continually <i>and</i> hear your wisdom.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9089G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9089G\"></sup>Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who delighted in you to set you on the throne of Israel; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9089H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9089H\"></sup>because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loved Israel forever, therefore He made you king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9089I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9089I\"></sup>to do justice and righteousness.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9090J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9090J\"></sup>She gave the king a hundred and twenty talents of gold, and a very great <i>amount</i> of spices and precious stones. Never again did such abundance of spices come in as that which the queen of Sheba gave King Solomon.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9091K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9091K\"></sup>Also the ships of Hiram, which brought gold from Ophir, brought in from Ophir a very great <i>number of</i> almug trees and precious stones.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9092L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9092L\"></sup>The king made of the almug trees supports for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for the king’s house, also lyres and harps for the singers; such almug trees have not come in <i>again</i> nor have they been seen to this day.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>King Solomon gave to the queen of Sheba all her desire which she requested, besides what he gave her according to his royal bounty. Then she turned and went to her own land together with her servants.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9094M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9094M\"></sup>Now the weight of gold which came in to Solomon in one year was 666 talents of gold,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>besides <i>that</i> from the traders and the wares of the merchants and all the kings of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9095N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9095N\"></sup>Arabs and the governors of the country.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9096O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9096O\"></sup>King Solomon made 200 large shields of beaten gold, using 600 <i>shekels of</i> gold on each large shield.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><i>He made</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9097P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9097P\"></sup>300 shields of beaten gold, using three minas of gold on each shield, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9097Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9097Q\"></sup>the king put them in the house of the forest of Lebanon.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Moreover, the king made a great throne of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9098R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9098R\"></sup>ivory and overlaid it with refined gold.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><i>There were</i> six steps to the throne and a round top to the throne at its rear, and arms on each side of the seat, and two lions standing beside the arms.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Twelve lions were standing there on the six steps on the one side and on the other; nothing like <i>it</i> was made for any other kingdom.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>All King Solomon’s drinking vessels <i>were</i> of gold, and all the vessels of the house of the forest of Lebanon <i>were</i> of pure gold. None was of silver; it was not considered valuable in the days of Solomon.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9102S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9102S\"></sup>the king had at sea the ships of Tarshish with the ships of Hiram; once every three years the ships of Tarshish came bringing gold and silver, ivory and apes and peacocks.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9103T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9103T\"></sup>So King Solomon became greater than all the kings of the earth in riches and in wisdom.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>All the earth was seeking the presence of Solomon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9104U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9104U\"></sup>to hear his wisdom which God had put in his heart.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9105V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9105V\"></sup>They brought every man his gift, articles of silver and gold, garments, weapons, spices, horses, and mules, so much year by year.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9106W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9106W\"></sup>Now Solomon gathered chariots and horsemen; and he had 1,400 chariots and 12,000 horsemen, and he stationed them in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9106X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9106X\"></sup>chariot cities and with the king in Jerusalem.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9107Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9107Y\"></sup>The king made silver <i>as common</i> as stones in Jerusalem, and he made cedars as plentiful as sycamore trees that are in the lowland.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9108Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9108Z\"></sup>Also Solomon’s import of horses was from Egypt and Kue, <i>and</i> the king’s merchants procured <i>them</i> from Kue for a price.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>A chariot was imported from Egypt for 600 <i>shekels</i> of silver, and a horse for 150; and by the same means they exported them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9109AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9109AA\"></sup>to all the kings of the Hittites and to the kings of the Arameans."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9110A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9110A\"></sup>King Solomon loved many foreign women along with the daughter of Pharaoh: Moabite, Ammonite, Edomite, Sidonian, and Hittite women,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>from the nations concerning which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said to the sons of Israel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9111B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9111B\"></sup>You shall not associate with them, nor shall they associate with you, <i>for</i> they will surely turn your heart away after their gods.” Solomon held fast to these in love.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9112C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9112C\"></sup>He had seven hundred wives, princesses, and three hundred concubines, and his wives turned his heart away.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For when Solomon was old, his wives turned his heart away after other gods; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9113D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9113D\"></sup>his heart was not wholly devoted to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, as the heart of David his father <i>had been</i>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For Solomon went after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9114E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9114E\"></sup>Ashtoreth the goddess of the Sidonians and after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9114F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9114F\"></sup>Milcom the detestable idol of the Ammonites.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Solomon did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and did not follow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fully, as David his father <i>had done</i>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Solomon built a high place for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9116G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9116G\"></sup>Chemosh the detestable idol of Moab, on the mountain which is east of Jerusalem, and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9116H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9116H\"></sup>Molech the detestable idol of the sons of Ammon.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Thus also he did for all his foreign wives, who burned incense and sacrificed to their gods.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9118I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9118I\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was angry with Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9118J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9118J\"></sup>because his heart was turned away from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9118K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9118K\"></sup>who had appeared to him twice,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9119L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9119L\"></sup>had commanded him concerning this thing, that he should not go after other gods; but he did not observe what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Solomon, “Because you have done this, and you have not kept My covenant and My statutes, which I have commanded you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9120M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9120M\"></sup>I will surely tear the kingdom from you, and will give it to your servant.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Nevertheless I will not do it in your days for the sake of your father David, <i>but</i> I will tear it out of the hand of your son.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>However, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9122N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9122N\"></sup>I will not tear away all the kingdom, <i>but</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9122O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9122O\"></sup>I will give one tribe to your son for the sake of My servant David and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9122P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9122P\"></sup>for the sake of Jerusalem which I have chosen.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> raised up an adversary to Solomon, Hadad the Edomite; he was of the royal line in Edom.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For it came about, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9124Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9124Q\"></sup>when David was in Edom, and Joab the commander of the army had gone up to bury the slain, and had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9124R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9124R\"></sup>struck down every male in Edom",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>(for Joab and all Israel stayed there six months, until he had cut off every male in Edom),",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>that Hadad fled to Egypt, he and certain Edomites of his father’s servants with him, while Hadad <i>was</i> a young boy.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They arose from Midian and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9127S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9127S\"></sup>Paran; and they took men with them from Paran and came to Egypt, to Pharaoh king of Egypt, who gave him a house and assigned him food and gave him land.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now Hadad found great favor before Pharaoh, so that he gave him in marriage the sister of his own wife, the sister of Tahpenes the queen.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The sister of Tahpenes bore his son Genubath, whom Tahpenes weaned in Pharaoh’s house; and Genubath was in Pharaoh’s house among the sons of Pharaoh.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9130T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9130T\"></sup>when Hadad heard in Egypt that David slept with his fathers and that Joab the commander of the army was dead, Hadad said to Pharaoh, “Send me away, that I may go to my own country.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to him, “But what have you lacked with me, that behold, you are seeking to go to your own country?” And he answered, “Nothing; nevertheless you must surely let me go.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9132U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9132U\"></sup>God also raised up <i>another</i> adversary to him, Rezon the son of Eliada, who had fled from his lord <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9132V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9132V\"></sup>Hadadezer king of Zobah.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He gathered men to himself and became leader of a marauding band, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9133W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9133W\"></sup>after David slew them of <i>Zobah</i>; and they went to Damascus and stayed there, and reigned in Damascus.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So he was an adversary to Israel all the days of Solomon, along with the evil that Hadad <i>did</i>; and he abhorred Israel and reigned over Aram.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9135X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9135X\"></sup>Jeroboam the son of Nebat, an Ephraimite of Zeredah, Solomon’s servant, whose mother’s name was Zeruah, a widow, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9135Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9135Y\"></sup>also rebelled against the king.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now this was the reason why he rebelled against the king: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9136Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9136Z\"></sup>Solomon built the Millo, <i>and</i> closed up the breach of the city of his father David.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now the man Jeroboam was a valiant warrior, and when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9137AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9137AA\"></sup>Solomon saw that the young man was industrious, he appointed him over all the forced labor of the house of Joseph.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>It came about at that time, when Jeroboam went out of Jerusalem, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9138AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9138AB\"></sup>the prophet Ahijah the Shilonite found him on the road. Now Ahijah had clothed himself with a new cloak; and both of them were alone in the field.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9139AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9139AC\"></sup>Ahijah took hold of the new cloak which was on him and tore it into twelve pieces.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He said to Jeroboam, “Take for yourself ten pieces; for thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, ‘Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9140AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9140AD\"></sup>I will tear the kingdom out of the hand of Solomon and give you ten tribes",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>(<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9141AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9141AE\"></sup>but he will have one tribe, for the sake of My servant David and for the sake of Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9141AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9141AF\"></sup>the city which I have chosen from all the tribes of Israel),",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>because they have forsaken Me, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9142AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9142AG\"></sup>have worshiped Ashtoreth the goddess of the Sidonians, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9142AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9142AH\"></sup>Chemosh the god of Moab, and Milcom the god of the sons of Ammon; and they have not walked in My ways, doing what is right in My sight and <i>observing</i> My statutes and My ordinances, as his father David <i>did</i>.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Nevertheless I will not take the whole kingdom out of his hand, but I will make him ruler all the days of his life, for the sake of My servant David whom I chose, who observed My commandments and My statutes;",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9144AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9144AI\"></sup>I will take the kingdom from his son’s hand and give it to you, <i>even</i> ten tribes.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9145AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9145AJ\"></sup>to his son I will give one tribe, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9145AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9145AK\"></sup>that My servant David may have a lamp always before Me in Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9145AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9145AL\"></sup>the city where I have chosen for Myself to put My name.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>I will take you, and you shall reign over whatever you desire, and you shall be king over Israel.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then it will be, that if you listen to all that I command you and walk in My ways, and do what is right in My sight by observing My statutes and My commandments, as My servant David did, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9147AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9147AM\"></sup>I will be with you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9147AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9147AN\"></sup>build you an enduring house as I built for David, and I will give Israel to you.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Thus I will afflict the descendants of David for this, but not always.’”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Solomon sought therefore to put Jeroboam to death; but Jeroboam arose and fled to Egypt to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9149AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9149AO\"></sup>Shishak king of Egypt, and he was in Egypt until the death of Solomon.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9150AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9150AP\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Solomon and whatever he did, and his wisdom, are they not written in the book of the acts of Solomon?",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9151AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9151AQ\"></sup>the time that Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel was forty years.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9152AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9152AR\"></sup>slept with his fathers and was buried in the city of his father David, and his son <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9152AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9152AS\"></sup>Rehoboam reigned in his place."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9153A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9153A\"></sup>Then Rehoboam went to Shechem, for all Israel had come to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9153B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9153B\"></sup>Shechem to make him king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9154C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9154C\"></sup>when Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard <i>of it</i>, he was living in Egypt (for he was yet in Egypt, where he had fled from the presence of King Solomon).",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then they sent and called him, and Jeroboam and all the assembly of Israel came and spoke to Rehoboam, saying,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9156D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9156D\"></sup>Your father made our yoke hard; now therefore lighten the hard service of your father and his heavy yoke which he put on us, and we will serve you.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then he said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9157E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9157E\"></sup>Depart for three days, then return to me.” So the people departed.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>King Rehoboam <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9158F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9158F\"></sup>consulted with the elders who had served his father Solomon while he was still alive, saying, “How do you counsel <i>me</i> to answer this people?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then they spoke to him, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9159G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9159G\"></sup>If you will be a servant to this people today, and will serve them and grant them their petition, and speak good words to them, then they will be your servants forever.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But he forsook the counsel of the elders which they had given him, and consulted with the young men who grew up with him and served him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So he said to them, “What counsel do you give that we may answer this people who have spoken to me, saying, ‘Lighten the yoke which your father put on us’?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The young men who grew up with him spoke to him, saying, “Thus you shall say to this people who spoke to you, saying, ‘Your father made our yoke heavy, now you make it lighter for us!’ But you shall speak to them, ‘My little finger is thicker than my father’s loins!",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Whereas my father loaded you with a heavy yoke, I will add to your yoke; my father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with scorpions.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam on the third day as the king had directed, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9164H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9164H\"></sup>Return to me on the third day.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The king answered the people harshly, for he forsook the advice of the elders which they had given him,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and he spoke to them according to the advice of the young men, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9166I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9166I\"></sup>My father made your yoke heavy, but I will add to your yoke; my father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with scorpions.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the king did not listen to the people; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9167J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9167J\"></sup>for it was a turn <i>of events</i> from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9167K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9167K\"></sup>that He might establish His word, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke through Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When all Israel <i>saw</i> that the king did not listen to them, the people answered the king, saying,“What portion do we have in David?<i>We have</i> no inheritance in the son of Jesse;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9168L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9168L\"></sup>To your tents, O Israel!Now look after your own house, David!”So Israel departed to their tents.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9169M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9169M\"></sup>as for the sons of Israel who lived in the cities of Judah, Rehoboam reigned over them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then King Rehoboam sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9170N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9170N\"></sup>Adoram, who was over the forced labor, and all Israel stoned him to death. And King Rehoboam made haste to mount his chariot to flee to Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9171O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9171O\"></sup>So Israel has been in rebellion against the house of David to this day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>It came about when all Israel heard that Jeroboam had returned, that they sent and called him to the assembly and made him king over all Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9172P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9172P\"></sup>None but the tribe of Judah followed the house of David.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9173Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9173Q\"></sup>Now when Rehoboam had come to Jerusalem, he assembled all the house of Judah and the tribe of Benjamin, 180,000 chosen men who were warriors, to fight against the house of Israel to restore the kingdom to Rehoboam the son of Solomon.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the word of God came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9174R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9174R\"></sup>Shemaiah the man of God, saying,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Speak to Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and to all the house of Judah and Benjamin and to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9175S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9175S\"></sup>rest of the people, saying,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “You must not go up and fight against your relatives the sons of Israel; return every man to his house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9176T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9176T\"></sup>for this thing has come from Me.”’” So they listened to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and returned and went <i>their way</i> according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9177U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9177U\"></sup>Jeroboam built Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim, and lived there. And he went out from there and built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9177V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9177V\"></sup>Penuel.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Jeroboam said in his heart, “Now the kingdom will return to the house of David.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9179W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9179W\"></sup>If this people go up to offer sacrifices in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Jerusalem, then the heart of this people will return to their lord, <i>even</i> to Rehoboam king of Judah; and they will kill me and return to Rehoboam king of Judah.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So the king consulted, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9180X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9180X\"></sup>made two golden <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9180Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9180Y\"></sup>calves, and he said to them, “It is too much for you to go up to Jerusalem; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9180Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9180Z\"></sup>behold your gods, O Israel, that brought you up from the land of Egypt.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He set <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9181AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9181AA\"></sup>one in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9181AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9181AB\"></sup>Bethel, and the other he put in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9181AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9181AC\"></sup>Dan.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9182AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9182AD\"></sup>this thing became a sin, for the people went <i>to worship</i> before the one as far as Dan.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9183AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9183AE\"></sup>he made houses on high places, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9183AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9183AF\"></sup>made priests from among all the people who were not of the sons of Levi.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Jeroboam instituted a feast in the eighth month on the fifteenth day of the month, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9184AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9184AG\"></sup>like the feast which is in Judah, and he went up to the altar; thus he did in Bethel, sacrificing to the calves which he had made. And he stationed in Bethel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9184AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9184AH\"></sup>the priests of the high places which he had made.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then he went up to the altar which he had made in Bethel on the fifteenth day in the eighth month, even in the month which he had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9185AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9185AI\"></sup>devised in his own heart; and he instituted a feast for the sons of Israel and went up to the altar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9185AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9185AJ\"></sup>to burn incense."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>Now behold, there came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9186A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9186A\"></sup>a man of God from Judah to Bethel by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, while Jeroboam was standing by the altar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9186B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9186B\"></sup>to burn incense.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9187C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9187C\"></sup>He cried against the altar by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and said, “O altar, altar, thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Behold, a son shall be born to the house of David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9187D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9187D\"></sup>Josiah by name; and on you he shall sacrifice the priests of the high places who burn incense on you, and human bones shall be burned on you.’”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then he gave a sign the same day, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9188E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9188E\"></sup>This is the sign which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken, ‘Behold, the altar shall be split apart and the ashes which are on it shall be poured out.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now when the king heard the saying of the man of God, which he cried against the altar in Bethel, Jeroboam stretched out his hand from the altar, saying, “Seize him.” But his hand which he stretched out against him dried up, so that he could not draw it back to himself.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The altar also was split apart and the ashes were poured out from the altar, according to the sign which the man of God had given by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The king said to the man of God, “Please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9191F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9191F\"></sup>entreat the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and pray for me, that my hand may be restored to me.” So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9191G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9191G\"></sup>the man of God entreated the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the king’s hand was restored to him, and it became as it was before.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the king said to the man of God, “Come home with me and refresh yourself, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9192H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9192H\"></sup>I will give you a reward.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But the man of God said to the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9193I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9193I\"></sup>If you were to give me half your house I would not go with you, nor would I eat bread or drink water in this place.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For so it was commanded me by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, ‘You shall eat no bread, nor drink water, nor return by the way which you came.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So he went another way and did not return by the way which he came to Bethel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9196J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9196J\"></sup>an old prophet was living in Bethel; and his sons came and told him all the deeds which the man of God had done that day in Bethel; the words which he had spoken to the king, these also they related to their father.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Their father said to them, “Which way did he go?” Now his sons had seen the way which the man of God who came from Judah had gone.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then he said to his sons, “Saddle the donkey for me.” So they saddled the donkey for him and he rode away on it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he went after the man of God and found him sitting under an oak; and he said to him, “Are you the man of God who came from Judah?” And he said, “I am.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then he said to him, “Come home with me and eat bread.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9201K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9201K\"></sup>I cannot return with you, nor go with you, nor will I eat bread or drink water with you in this place.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For a command <i>came</i> to me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9202L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9202L\"></sup>by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘You shall eat no bread, nor drink water there; do not return by going the way which you came.’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9203M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9203M\"></sup>I also am a prophet like you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9203N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9203N\"></sup>an angel spoke to me by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, ‘Bring him back with you to your house, that he may eat bread and drink water.’” <i>But</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9203O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9203O\"></sup>he lied to him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So he went back with him, and ate bread in his house and drank water.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now it came about, as they were sitting down at the table, that the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to the prophet who had brought him back;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and he cried to the man of God who came from Judah, saying, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Because you have disobeyed the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and have not observed the commandment which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God commanded you,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>but have returned and eaten bread and drunk water in the place of which He said to you, “Eat no bread and drink no water”; your body shall not come to the grave of your fathers.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>It came about after he had eaten bread and after he had drunk, that he saddled the donkey for him, for the prophet whom he had brought back.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now when he had gone, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9209P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9209P\"></sup>a lion met him on the way and killed him, and his body was thrown on the road, with the donkey standing beside it; the lion also was standing beside the body.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And behold, men passed by and saw the body thrown on the road, and the lion standing beside the body; so they came and told <i>it</i> in the city where <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9210Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9210Q\"></sup>the old prophet lived.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now when the prophet who brought him back from the way heard <i>it</i>, he said, “It is the man of God, who disobeyed the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given him to the lion, which has torn him and killed him, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which He spoke to him.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then he spoke to his sons, saying, “Saddle the donkey for me.” And they saddled <i>it</i>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He went and found his body thrown on the road with the donkey and the lion standing beside the body; the lion had not eaten the body nor torn the donkey.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So the prophet took up the body of the man of God and laid it on the donkey and brought it back, and he came to the city of the old prophet to mourn and to bury him.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He laid his body in his own grave, and they mourned over him, <i>saying</i>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9215R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9215R\"></sup>Alas, my brother!”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>After he had buried him, he spoke to his sons, saying, “When I die, bury me in the grave in which the man of God is buried; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9216S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9216S\"></sup>lay my bones beside his bones.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9217T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9217T\"></sup>For the thing shall surely come to pass which he cried by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> against the altar in Bethel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9217U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9217U\"></sup>against all the houses of the high places which are in the cities of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9217V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9217V\"></sup>Samaria.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>After this event Jeroboam did not return from his evil way, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9218W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9218W\"></sup>again he made priests of the high places from among all the people; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9218X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9218X\"></sup>any who would, he ordained, to be priests of the high places.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9219Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9219Y\"></sup>This event became sin to the house of Jeroboam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9219Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9219Z\"></sup>even to blot <i>it</i> out and destroy <i>it</i> from off the face of the earth."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>At that time Abijah the son of Jeroboam became sick.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jeroboam said to his wife, “Arise now, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9221A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9221A\"></sup>disguise yourself so that they will not know that you are the wife of Jeroboam, and go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9221B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9221B\"></sup>Shiloh; behold, Ahijah the prophet is there, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9221C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9221C\"></sup>spoke concerning me <i>that I would be</i> king over this people.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9222D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9222D\"></sup>Take ten loaves with you, <i>some</i> cakes and a jar of honey, and go to him. He will tell you what will happen to the boy.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jeroboam’s wife did so, and arose and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9223E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9223E\"></sup>Shiloh, and came to the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9223F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9223F\"></sup>Ahijah. Now Ahijah could not see, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9223G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9223G\"></sup>for his eyes were dim because of his age.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said to Ahijah, “Behold, the wife of Jeroboam is coming to inquire of you concerning her son, for he is sick. You shall say thus and thus to her, for it will be when she arrives that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9224H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9224H\"></sup>she will pretend to be another woman.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Ahijah heard the sound of her feet coming in the doorway, he said, “Come in, wife of Jeroboam, why do you pretend to be another woman? For I am sent to you <i>with</i> a harsh <i>message</i>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Go, say to Jeroboam, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9226I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9226I\"></sup>Because I exalted you from among the people and made you leader over My people Israel,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9227J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9227J\"></sup>tore the kingdom away from the house of David and gave it to you—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9227K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9227K\"></sup>yet you have not been like My servant David, who kept My commandments and who followed Me with all his heart, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9227L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9227L\"></sup>to do only that which was right in My sight;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>you also have done more evil than all who were before you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9228M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9228M\"></sup>have gone and made for yourself other gods and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9228N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9228N\"></sup>molten images to provoke Me to anger, and have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9228O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9228O\"></sup>cast Me behind your back—",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>therefore behold, I am bringing calamity on the house of Jeroboam, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9229P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9229P\"></sup>will cut off from Jeroboam every male person, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9229Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9229Q\"></sup>both bond and free in Israel, and I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9229R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9229R\"></sup>will make a clean sweep of the house of Jeroboam, as one sweeps away dung until it is all gone.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9230S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9230S\"></sup>Anyone belonging to Jeroboam who dies in the city the dogs will eat. And he who dies in the field the birds of the heavens will eat; for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken <i>it</i>.”’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now you, arise, go to your house. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9231T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9231T\"></sup>When your feet enter the city the child will die.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>All Israel shall mourn for him and bury him, for he alone of Jeroboam’s <i>family</i> will come to the grave, because in him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9232U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9232U\"></sup>something good was found toward the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel in the house of Jeroboam.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9233V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9233V\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will raise up for Himself a king over Israel who will cut off the house of Jeroboam this day and from now on.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will strike Israel, as a reed is shaken in the water; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9234W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9234W\"></sup>He will uproot Israel from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9234X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9234X\"></sup>this good land which He gave to their fathers, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9234Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9234Y\"></sup>will scatter them beyond the <i>Euphrates</i> River, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9234Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9234Z\"></sup>because they have made their Asherim, provoking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to anger.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He will give up Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9235AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9235AA\"></sup>on account of the sins of Jeroboam, which he committed and with which he made Israel to sin.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Jeroboam’s wife arose and departed and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9236AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9236AB\"></sup>Tirzah. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9236AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9236AC\"></sup>As she was entering the threshold of the house, the child died.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9237AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9237AD\"></sup>All Israel buried him and mourned for him, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which He spoke through His servant Ahijah the prophet.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jeroboam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9238AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9238AE\"></sup>how he made war and how he reigned, behold, they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The time that Jeroboam reigned <i>was</i> twenty-two years; and he slept with his fathers, and Nadab his son reigned in his place.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9240AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9240AF\"></sup>Now Rehoboam the son of Solomon reigned in Judah. Rehoboam was forty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9240AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9240AG\"></sup>the city which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had chosen from all the tribes of Israel to put His name there. And his mother’s name was Naamah the Ammonitess.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9241AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9241AH\"></sup>Judah did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9241AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9241AI\"></sup>provoked Him to jealousy more than all that their fathers had done, with the sins which they committed.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For they also built for themselves <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9242AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9242AJ\"></sup>high places and <i>sacred</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9242AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9242AK\"></sup>pillars and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9242AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9242AL\"></sup>Asherim on every high hill and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9242AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9242AM\"></sup>beneath every luxuriant tree.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>There were also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9243AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9243AN\"></sup>male cult prostitutes in the land. They did according to all the abominations of the nations which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> dispossessed before the sons of Israel.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9244AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9244AO\"></sup>Now it happened in the fifth year of King Rehoboam, that Shishak the king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He took away the treasures of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the treasures of the king’s house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9245AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9245AP\"></sup>he took everything, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9245AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9245AQ\"></sup>even taking all the shields of gold which Solomon had made.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So King Rehoboam made shields of bronze in their place, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9246AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9246AR\"></sup>committed them to the care of the commanders of the guard who guarded the doorway of the king’s house.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then it happened as often as the king entered the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that the guards would carry them and would bring them back into the guards’ room.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9248AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9248AS\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Rehoboam and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9249AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9249AT\"></sup>There was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam continually.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And Rehoboam slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the city of David; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9250AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9250AU\"></sup>his mother’s name was Naamah the Ammonitess. And Abijam his son became king in his place."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9251A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9251A\"></sup>Now in the eighteenth year of King Jeroboam, the son of Nebat, Abijam became king over Judah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He reigned three years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9252B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9252B\"></sup>Maacah the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9252C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9252C\"></sup>Abishalom.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He walked in all the sins of his father which he had committed before him; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9253D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9253D\"></sup>his heart was not wholly devoted to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, like the heart of his father David.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But for David’s sake the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God gave him a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9254E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9254E\"></sup>lamp in Jerusalem, to raise up his son after him and to establish Jerusalem;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9255F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9255F\"></sup>because David did what was right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and had not turned aside from anything that He commanded him all the days of his life, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9255G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9255G\"></sup>except in the case of Uriah the Hittite.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9256H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9256H\"></sup>There was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all the days of his life.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9257I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9257I\"></sup>the rest of the acts of Abijam and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9257J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9257J\"></sup>And there was war between Abijam and Jeroboam.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9258K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9258K\"></sup>And Abijam slept with his fathers and they buried him in the city of David; and Asa his son became king in his place.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So in the twentieth year of Jeroboam the king of Israel, Asa began to reign as king of Judah.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He reigned forty-one years in Jerusalem; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9260L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9260L\"></sup>his mother’s name was Maacah the daughter of Abishalom.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9261M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9261M\"></sup>Asa did what was right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, like David his father.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9262N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9262N\"></sup>He also put away the male cult prostitutes from the land and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9262O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9262O\"></sup>removed all the idols which his fathers had made.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9263P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9263P\"></sup>He also removed Maacah his mother from <i>being</i> queen mother, because she had made a horrid image as an Asherah; and Asa cut down her horrid image and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9263Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9263Q\"></sup>burned <i>it</i> at the brook Kidron.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9264R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9264R\"></sup>But the high places were not taken away; nevertheless <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9264S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9264S\"></sup>the heart of Asa was wholly devoted to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all his days.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9265T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9265T\"></sup>He brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the dedicated things of his father and his own dedicated things: silver and gold and utensils.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9266U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9266U\"></sup>Now there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9267V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9267V\"></sup>Baasha king of Israel went up against Judah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9267W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9267W\"></sup>fortified Ramah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9267X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9267X\"></sup>in order to prevent <i>anyone</i> from going out or coming in to Asa king of Judah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9268Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9268Y\"></sup>Asa took all the silver and the gold which were left in the treasuries of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the treasuries of the king’s house, and delivered them into the hand of his servants. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9268Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9268Z\"></sup>King Asa sent them to Ben-hadad the son of Tabrimmon, the son of Hezion, king of Aram, who lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9268AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9268AA\"></sup>Damascus, saying,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“<i>Let there be</i> a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9269AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9269AB\"></sup>treaty between you and me, <i>as</i> between my father and your father. Behold, I have sent you a present of silver and gold; go, break your treaty with Baasha king of Israel so that he will withdraw from me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Ben-hadad listened to King Asa and sent the commanders of his armies against the cities of Israel, and conquered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9270AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9270AC\"></sup>Ijon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9270AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9270AD\"></sup>Dan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9270AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9270AE\"></sup>Abel-beth-maacah and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9270AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9270AF\"></sup>Chinneroth, besides all the land of Naphtali.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When Baasha heard <i>of it</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9271AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9271AG\"></sup>he ceased fortifying Ramah and remained in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9271AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9271AH\"></sup>Tirzah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then King Asa made a proclamation to all Judah—none was exempt—and they carried away the stones of Ramah and its timber with which Baasha had built. And King Asa built with them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9272AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9272AI\"></sup>Geba of Benjamin and Mizpah.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9273AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9273AJ\"></sup>Now the rest of all the acts of Asa and all his might and all that he did and the cities which he built, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? But in the time of his old age he was diseased in his feet.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Asa slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the city of David his father; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9274AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9274AK\"></sup>Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his place.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9275AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9275AL\"></sup>Nadab the son of Jeroboam became king over Israel in the second year of Asa king of Judah, and he reigned over Israel two years.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9276AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9276AM\"></sup>walked in the way of his father and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9276AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9276AN\"></sup>in his sin which he made Israel sin.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9277AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9277AO\"></sup>Baasha the son of Ahijah of the house of Issachar conspired against him, and Baasha struck him down at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9277AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9277AP\"></sup>Gibbethon, which belonged to the Philistines, while Nadab and all Israel were laying siege to Gibbethon.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Baasha killed him in the third year of Asa king of Judah and reigned in his place.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>It came about as soon as he was king, he struck down all the household of Jeroboam. He did not leave to Jeroboam any persons alive, until he had destroyed them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9279AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9279AQ\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which He spoke by His servant Ahijah the Shilonite,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><i>and</i> because of the sins of Jeroboam which he sinned, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9280AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9280AR\"></sup>which he made Israel sin, because of his provocation with which he provoked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel to anger.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9281AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9281AS\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Nadab and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9282AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9282AT\"></sup>There was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In the third year of Asa king of Judah, Baasha the son of Ahijah became king over all Israel at Tirzah, <i>and reigned</i> twenty-four years.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9284AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9284AU\"></sup>walked in the way of Jeroboam and in his sin which he made Israel sin."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Now the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9285A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9285A\"></sup>Jehu the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9285B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9285B\"></sup>Hanani against Baasha, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Inasmuch as I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9286C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9286C\"></sup>exalted you from the dust and made you leader over My people Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9286D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9286D\"></sup>you have walked in the way of Jeroboam and have made My people Israel sin, provoking Me to anger with their sins,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9287E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9287E\"></sup>I will consume <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9287F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9287F\"></sup>Baasha and his house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9287G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9287G\"></sup>I will make your house like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9288H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9288H\"></sup>Anyone of Baasha who dies in the city the dogs will eat, and anyone of his who dies in the field the birds of the heavens will eat.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9289I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9289I\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Baasha and what he did and his might, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Baasha slept with his fathers and was buried in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9290J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9290J\"></sup>Tirzah, and Elah his son became king in his place.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Moreover, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> through <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9291K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9291K\"></sup>the prophet Jehu the son of Hanani also came against Baasha and his household, both because of all the evil which he did in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, provoking Him to anger with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9291L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9291L\"></sup>the work of his hands, in being like the house of Jeroboam, and because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9291M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9291M\"></sup>he struck it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In the twenty-sixth year of Asa king of Judah, Elah the son of Baasha became king over Israel at Tirzah, <i>and reigned</i> two years.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>His servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9293N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9293N\"></sup>Zimri, commander of half his chariots, conspired against him. Now he <i>was</i> at Tirzah drinking himself drunk in the house of Arza, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9293O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9293O\"></sup>who <i>was</i> over the household at Tirzah.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Zimri went in and struck him and put him to death in the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, and became king in his place.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>It came about when he became king, as soon as he sat on his throne, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9295P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9295P\"></sup>he killed all the household of Baasha; he did not leave a single male, neither of his relatives nor of his friends.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Thus Zimri destroyed all the household of Baasha, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9296Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9296Q\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which He spoke against Baasha through <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9296R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9296R\"></sup>Jehu the prophet,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>for all the sins of Baasha and the sins of Elah his son, which they sinned and which they made Israel sin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9297S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9297S\"></sup>provoking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel to anger with their idols.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9298T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9298T\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Elah and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, Zimri reigned seven days at Tirzah. Now the people were camped against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9299U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9299U\"></sup>Gibbethon, which belonged to the Philistines.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The people who were camped heard it said, “Zimri has conspired and has also struck down the king.” Therefore all Israel made Omri, the commander of the army, king over Israel that day in the camp.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Omri and all Israel with him went up from Gibbethon and besieged Tirzah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When Zimri saw that the city was taken, he went into the citadel of the king’s house and burned the king’s house over him with fire, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9302V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9302V\"></sup>died,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>because of his sins which he sinned, doing evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9303W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9303W\"></sup>walking in the way of Jeroboam, and in his sin which he did, making Israel sin.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9304X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9304X\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Zimri and his conspiracy which he carried out, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the people of Israel were divided into two parts: half of the people followed Tibni the son of Ginath, to make him king; the <i>other</i> half followed Omri.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the people who followed Omri prevailed over the people who followed Tibni the son of Ginath. And Tibni died and Omri became king.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In the thirty-first year of Asa king of Judah, Omri became king over Israel <i>and reigned</i> twelve years; he reigned six years at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9307Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9307Y\"></sup>Tirzah.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He bought the hill Samaria from Shemer for two talents of silver; and he built on the hill, and named the city which he built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9308Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9308Z\"></sup>Samaria, after the name of Shemer, the owner of the hill.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9309AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9309AA\"></sup>Omri did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9309AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9309AB\"></sup>acted more wickedly than all who <i>were</i> before him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9310AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9310AC\"></sup>walked in all the way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat and in his sins which he made Israel sin, provoking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel with their idols.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Omri which he did and his might which he showed, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Omri slept with his fathers and was buried in Samaria; and Ahab his son became king in his place.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now Ahab the son of Omri became king over Israel in the thirty-eighth year of Asa king of Judah, and Ahab the son of Omri reigned over Israel in Samaria twenty-two years.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Ahab the son of Omri did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9314AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9314AD\"></sup>more than all who were before him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>It came about, as though it had been a trivial thing for him to walk in the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9315AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9315AE\"></sup>he married Jezebel the daughter of Ethbaal king of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9315AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9315AF\"></sup>Sidonians, and went to serve Baal and worshiped him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So he erected an altar for Baal in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9316AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9316AG\"></sup>the house of Baal which he built in Samaria.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Ahab also made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9317AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9317AH\"></sup>the Asherah. Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9317AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9317AI\"></sup>Ahab did more to provoke the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel than all the kings of Israel who were before him.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9318AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9318AJ\"></sup>In his days Hiel the Bethelite built Jericho; he laid its foundations with the <i>loss of</i> Abiram his firstborn, and set up its gates with the <i>loss of</i> his youngest son Segub, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which He spoke by Joshua the son of Nun."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Now Elijah the Tishbite, who was of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9319A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9319A\"></sup>the settlers of Gilead, said to Ahab, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9319B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9319B\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel lives, before whom I stand, surely <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9319C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9319C\"></sup>there shall be neither dew nor rain these years, except by my word.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him, saying,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Go away from here and turn eastward, and hide yourself by the brook Cherith, which is east of the Jordan.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>It shall be that you will drink of the brook, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9322D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9322D\"></sup>I have commanded the ravens to provide for you there.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So he went and did according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he went and lived by the brook Cherith, which is east of the Jordan.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The ravens brought him bread and meat in the morning and bread and meat in the evening, and he would drink from the brook.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>It happened after a while that the brook dried up, because there was no rain in the land.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him, saying,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Arise, go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9327E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9327E\"></sup>Zarephath, which belongs to Sidon, and stay there; behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9327F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9327F\"></sup>I have commanded a widow there to provide for you.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So he arose and went to Zarephath, and when he came to the gate of the city, behold, a widow was there gathering sticks; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9328G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9328G\"></sup>he called to her and said, “Please get me a little water in a jar, that I may drink.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As she was going to get <i>it</i>, he called to her and said, “Please bring me a piece of bread in your hand.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But she said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9330H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9330H\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God lives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9330I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9330I\"></sup>I have no bread, only a handful of flour in the bowl and a little oil in the jar; and behold, I am gathering a few sticks that I may go in and prepare for me and my son, that we may eat it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9330J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9330J\"></sup>die.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Elijah said to her, “Do not fear; go, do as you have said, but make me a little bread cake from it first and bring <i>it</i> out to me, and afterward you may make <i>one</i> for yourself and for your son.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, ‘The bowl of flour shall not be exhausted, nor shall the jar of oil be empty, until the day that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sends rain on the face of the earth.’”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So she went and did according to the word of Elijah, and she and he and her household ate for <i>many</i> days.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The bowl of flour was not exhausted nor did the jar of oil become empty, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which He spoke through Elijah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now it came about after these things that the son of the woman, the mistress of the house, became sick; and his sickness was so severe that there was no breath left in him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So she said to Elijah, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9336K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9336K\"></sup>What do I have to do with you, O <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9336L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9336L\"></sup>man of God? You have come to me to bring my iniquity to remembrance and to put my son to death!”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He said to her, “Give me your son.” Then he took him from her bosom and carried him up to the upper room where he was living, and laid him on his own bed.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He called to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, have You also brought calamity to the widow with whom I am staying, by causing her son to die?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9339M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9339M\"></sup>Then he stretched himself upon the child three times, and called to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, I pray You, let this child’s life return to him.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard the voice of Elijah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9340N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9340N\"></sup>and the life of the child returned to him and he revived.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Elijah took the child and brought him down from the upper room into the house and gave him to his mother; and Elijah said, “See, your son is alive.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the woman said to Elijah, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9342O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9342O\"></sup>Now I know that you are a man of God and that the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in your mouth is truth.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Now it happened <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9343A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9343A\"></sup><i>after</i> many days that the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Elijah in the third year, saying, “Go, show yourself to Ahab, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9343B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9343B\"></sup>I will send rain on the face of the earth.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Elijah went to show himself to Ahab. Now the famine <i>was</i> severe in Samaria.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Ahab called Obadiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9345C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9345C\"></sup>who <i>was</i> over the household. (Now Obadiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9345D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9345D\"></sup>feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> greatly;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9346E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9346E\"></sup>when Jezebel destroyed the prophets of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Obadiah took a hundred prophets and hid them by fifties in a cave, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9346F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9346F\"></sup>provided them with bread and water.)",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Ahab said to Obadiah, “Go through the land to all the springs of water and to all the valleys; perhaps we will find grass and keep the horses and mules alive, and not have to kill some of the cattle.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So they divided the land between them to survey it; Ahab went one way by himself and Obadiah went another way by himself.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now as Obadiah was on the way, behold, Elijah met him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9349G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9349G\"></sup>and he recognized him and fell on his face and said, “Is this you, Elijah my master?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He said to him, “It is I. Go, say to your master, ‘Behold, Elijah <i>is here</i>.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He said, “What sin have I committed, that you are giving your servant into the hand of Ahab to put me to death?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9352H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9352H\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God lives, there is no nation or kingdom where my master has not sent to search for you; and when they said, ‘He is not <i>here</i>,’ he made the kingdom or nation swear that they could not find you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And now you are saying, ‘Go, say to your master, “Behold, Elijah <i>is here</i>.”’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>It will come about when I leave you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9354I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9354I\"></sup>that the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will carry you where I do not know; so when I come and tell Ahab and he cannot find you, he will kill me, although <i>I</i> your servant have feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from my youth.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9355J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9355J\"></sup>Has it not been told to my master what I did when Jezebel killed the prophets of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that I hid a hundred prophets of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by fifties in a cave, and provided them with bread and water?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And now you are saying, ‘Go, say to your master, “Behold, Elijah <i>is here</i>”’; he will then kill me.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Elijah said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9357K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9357K\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts lives, before whom I stand, I will surely show myself to him today.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Obadiah went to meet Ahab and told him; and Ahab went to meet Elijah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When Ahab saw Elijah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9359L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9359L\"></sup>Ahab said to him, “Is this you, you troubler of Israel?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He said, “I have not troubled Israel, but you and your father’s house <i>have</i>, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9360M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9360M\"></sup>you have forsaken the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9360N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9360N\"></sup>you have followed the Baals.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now then send <i>and</i> gather to me all Israel at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9361O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9361O\"></sup>Mount Carmel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9361P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9361P\"></sup><i>together</i> with 450 prophets of Baal and 400 prophets of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9361Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9361Q\"></sup>the Asherah, who eat at Jezebel’s table.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Ahab sent <i>a message</i> among all the sons of Israel and brought the prophets together at Mount Carmel.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Elijah came near to all the people and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9363R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9363R\"></sup>How long <i>will</i> you hesitate between two opinions? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9363S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9363S\"></sup>If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is God, follow Him; but if Baal, follow him.” But the people did not answer him a word.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Elijah said to the people, “I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9364T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9364T\"></sup>alone am left a prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but Baal’s prophets are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9364U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9364U\"></sup>450 men.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now let them give us two oxen; and let them choose one ox for themselves and cut it up, and place it on the wood, but put no fire <i>under it</i>; and I will prepare the other ox and lay it on the wood, and I will not put a fire <i>under it</i>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then you call on the name of your god, and I will call on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9366V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9366V\"></sup>the God who answers by fire, He is God.” And all the people said, “That is a good idea.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So Elijah said to the prophets of Baal, “Choose one ox for yourselves and prepare it first for you are many, and call on the name of your god, but put no fire <i>under it</i>.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then they took the ox which was given them and they prepared it and called on the name of Baal from morning until noon saying, “O Baal, answer us.” But there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9368W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9368W\"></sup>no voice and no one answered. And they leaped about the altar which they made.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>It came about at noon, that Elijah mocked them and said, “Call out with a loud voice, for he is a god; either he is occupied or gone aside, or is on a journey, or perhaps he is asleep and needs to be awakened.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So they cried with a loud voice and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9370X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9370X\"></sup>cut themselves according to their custom with swords and lances until the blood gushed out on them.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When midday was past, they raved <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9371Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9371Y\"></sup>until the time of the offering of the <i>evening</i> sacrifice; but there was no voice, no one answered, and no one paid attention.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Elijah said to all the people, “Come near to me.” So all the people came near to him. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9372Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9372Z\"></sup>he repaired the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which had been torn down.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Elijah took twelve stones according to the number of the tribes of the sons of Jacob, to whom the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had come, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9373AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9373AA\"></sup>Israel shall be your name.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So with the stones he built an altar in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9374AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9374AB\"></sup>the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he made a trench around the altar, large enough to hold two measures of seed.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9375AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9375AC\"></sup>Then he arranged the wood and cut the ox in pieces and laid <i>it</i> on the wood.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And he said, “Fill four pitchers with water and pour <i>it</i> on the burnt offering and on the wood.” And he said, “Do it a second time,” and they did it a second time. And he said, “Do it a third time,” and they did it a third time.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The water flowed around the altar and he also filled the trench with water.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9378AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9378AD\"></sup>At the time of the offering of the <i>evening</i> sacrifice, Elijah the prophet came near and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9378AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9378AE\"></sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Abraham, Isaac and Israel, today let it be known that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9378AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9378AF\"></sup>You are God in Israel and that I am Your servant and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9378AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9378AG\"></sup>I have done all these things at Your word.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Answer me, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, answer me, that this people may know that You, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, are God, and <i>that</i> You have turned their heart back again.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9380AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9380AH\"></sup>fire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fell and consumed the burnt offering and the wood and the stones and the dust, and licked up the water that was in the trench.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>When all the people saw it, they fell on their faces; and they said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9381AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9381AI\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, He is God; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, He is God.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Then Elijah said to them, “Seize the prophets of Baal; do not let one of them escape.” So they seized them; and Elijah brought them down to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9382AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9382AJ\"></sup>the brook Kishon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9382AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9382AK\"></sup>and slew them there.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Now Elijah said to Ahab, “Go up, eat and drink; for there is the sound of the roar of a <i>heavy</i> shower.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>So Ahab went up to eat and drink. But Elijah went up to the top of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9384AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9384AL\"></sup>Carmel; and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9384AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9384AM\"></sup>crouched down on the earth and put his face between his knees.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>He said to his servant, “Go up now, look toward the sea.” So he went up and looked and said, “There is nothing.” And he said, “Go back” seven times.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>It came about at the seventh <i>time</i>, that he said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9386AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9386AN\"></sup>a cloud as small as a man’s hand is coming up from the sea.” And he said, “Go up, say to Ahab, ‘Prepare <i>your chariot</i> and go down, so that the <i>heavy</i> shower does not stop you.’”",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>In a little while the sky grew black with clouds and wind, and there was a heavy shower. And Ahab rode and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9387AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9387AO\"></sup>Jezreel.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9388AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9388AP\"></sup>the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was on Elijah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9388AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9388AQ\"></sup>he girded up his loins and outran Ahab to Jezreel."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Now Ahab told Jezebel all that Elijah had done, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9389A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9389A\"></sup>how he had killed all the prophets with the sword.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Jezebel sent a messenger to Elijah, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9390B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9390B\"></sup>So may the gods do to me and even more, if I do not make your life as the life of one of them by tomorrow about this time.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he was afraid and arose and ran for his life and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9391C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9391C\"></sup>Beersheba, which belongs to Judah, and left his servant there.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But he himself went a day’s journey into the wilderness, and came and sat down under a juniper tree; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9392D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9392D\"></sup>he requested for himself that he might die, and said, “It is enough; now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, take my life, for I am not better than my fathers.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He lay down and slept under a juniper tree; and behold, there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9393E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9393E\"></sup>an angel touching him, and he said to him, “Arise, eat.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then he looked and behold, there was at his head a bread cake <i>baked on</i> hot stones, and a jar of water. So he ate and drank and lay down again.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came again a second time and touched him and said, “Arise, eat, because the journey is too great for you.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So he arose and ate and drank, and went in the strength of that food <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9396F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9396F\"></sup>forty days and forty nights to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9396G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9396G\"></sup>Horeb, the mountain of God.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then he came there to a cave and lodged there; and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9397H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9397H\"></sup>the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>came</i> to him, and He said to him, “What are you doing here, Elijah?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9398I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9398I\"></sup>I have been very zealous for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of hosts; for the sons of Israel have forsaken Your covenant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9398J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9398J\"></sup>torn down Your altars and killed Your prophets with the sword. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9398K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9398K\"></sup>I alone am left; and they seek my life, to take it away.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9399L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9399L\"></sup>Go forth and stand on the mountain before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And behold, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was passing by! And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9399M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9399M\"></sup>a great and strong wind was rending the mountains and breaking in pieces the rocks before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <i>but</i> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>was</i> not in the wind. And after the wind an earthquake, <i>but</i> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>was</i> not in the earthquake.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>After the earthquake a fire, <i>but</i> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>was</i> not in the fire; and after the fire <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9400N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9400N\"></sup>a sound of a gentle blowing.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When Elijah heard <i>it</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9401O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9401O\"></sup>he wrapped his face in his mantle and went out and stood in the entrance of the cave. And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9401P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9401P\"></sup>a voice <i>came</i> to him and said, “What are you doing here, Elijah?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9402Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9402Q\"></sup>I have been very zealous for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of hosts; for the sons of Israel have forsaken Your covenant, torn down Your altars and killed Your prophets with the sword. And I alone am left; and they seek my life, to take it away.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Go, return on your way to the wilderness of Damascus, and when you have arrived, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9403R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9403R\"></sup>you shall anoint Hazael king over Aram;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9404S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9404S\"></sup>Jehu the son of Nimshi you shall anoint king over Israel; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9404T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9404T\"></sup>Elisha the son of Shaphat of Abel-meholah you shall anoint as prophet in your place.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>It shall come about, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9405U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9405U\"></sup>one who escapes from the sword of Hazael, Jehu <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9405V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9405V\"></sup>shall put to death, and the one who escapes from the sword of Jehu, Elisha shall put to death.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9406W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9406W\"></sup>Yet I will leave 7,000 in Israel, all the knees that have not bowed to Baal and every mouth that has not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9406X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9406X\"></sup>kissed him.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So he departed from there and found Elisha the son of Shaphat, while he was plowing with twelve pairs <i>of oxen</i> before him, and he with the twelfth. And Elijah passed over to him and threw <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9407Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9407Y\"></sup>his mantle on him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He left the oxen and ran after Elijah and said, “Please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9408Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9408Z\"></sup>let me kiss my father and my mother, then I will follow you.” And he said to him, “Go back again, for what have I done to you?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So he returned from following him, and took the pair of oxen and sacrificed them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9409AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9409AA\"></sup>boiled their flesh with the implements of the oxen, and gave <i>it</i> to the people and they ate. Then he arose and followed Elijah and ministered to him."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9410A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9410A\"></sup>Ben-hadad king of Aram gathered all his army, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9410B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9410B\"></sup>and there <i>were</i> thirty-two kings with him, and horses and chariots. And he went up and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9410C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9410C\"></sup>besieged Samaria and fought against it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then he sent messengers to the city to Ahab king of Israel and said to him, “Thus says Ben-hadad,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>‘Your silver and your gold are mine; your most beautiful wives and children are also mine.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king of Israel replied, “It is according to your word, my lord, O king; I am yours, and all that I have.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the messengers returned and said, “Thus says Ben-hadad, ‘Surely, I sent to you saying, “You shall give me your silver and your gold and your wives and your children,”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>but about this time tomorrow I will send my servants to you, and they will search your house and the houses of your servants; and whatever is desirable in your eyes, they will take in their hand and carry away.’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the king of Israel called all the elders of the land and said, “Please observe and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9416D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9416D\"></sup>see how this man is looking for trouble; for he sent to me for my wives and my children and my silver and my gold, and I did not refuse him.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>All the elders and all the people said to him, “Do not listen or consent.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So he said to the messengers of Ben-hadad, “Tell my lord the king, ‘All that you sent for to your servant at the first I will do, but this thing I cannot do.’” And the messengers departed and brought him word again.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Ben-hadad sent to him and said, “May <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9419E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9419E\"></sup>the gods do so to me and more also, if the dust of Samaria will suffice for handfuls for all the people who follow me.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the king of Israel replied, “Tell <i>him</i>, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9420F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9420F\"></sup>Let not him who girds on <i>his armor</i> boast like him who takes <i>it</i> off.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When <i>Ben-hadad</i> heard this message, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9421G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9421G\"></sup>he was drinking with the kings in the temporary shelters, he said to his servants, “Station <i>yourselves</i>.” So they stationed <i>themselves</i> against the city.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now behold, a prophet approached Ahab king of Israel and said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Have you seen all this great multitude? Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9422H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9422H\"></sup>I will deliver them into your hand today, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9422I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9422I\"></sup>you shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Ahab said, “By whom?” So he said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘By the young men of the rulers of the provinces.’” Then he said, “Who shall begin the battle?” And he answered, “You.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then he mustered the young men of the rulers of the provinces, and there were 232; and after them he mustered all the people, <i>even</i> all the sons of Israel, 7,000.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They went out at noon, while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9425J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9425J\"></sup>Ben-hadad was drinking himself drunk in the temporary shelters with the thirty-two kings who helped him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The young men of the rulers of the provinces went out first; and Ben-hadad sent out and they told him, saying, “Men have come out from Samaria.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9427K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9427K\"></sup>Then he said, “If they have come out for peace, take them alive; or if they have come out for war, take them alive.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So these went out from the city, the young men of the rulers of the provinces, and the army which followed them.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They killed each his man; and the Arameans fled and Israel pursued them, and Ben-hadad king of Aram escaped on a horse with horsemen.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The king of Israel went out and struck the horses and chariots, and killed the Arameans with a great slaughter.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9431L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9431L\"></sup>the prophet came near to the king of Israel and said to him, “Go, strengthen yourself and observe and see what you have to do; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9431M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9431M\"></sup>at the turn of the year the king of Aram will come up against you.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now the servants of the king of Aram said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9432N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9432N\"></sup>Their gods are gods of the mountains, therefore they were stronger than we; but rather let us fight against them in the plain, <i>and</i> surely we will be stronger than they.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Do this thing: remove the kings, each from his place, and put captains in their place,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and muster an army like the army that you have lost, horse for horse, and chariot for chariot. Then we will fight against them in the plain, and surely we will be stronger than they.” And he listened to their voice and did so.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9435O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9435O\"></sup>At the turn of the year, Ben-hadad mustered the Arameans and went up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9435P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9435P\"></sup>Aphek to fight against Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The sons of Israel were mustered and were provisioned and went to meet them; and the sons of Israel camped before them like two little flocks of goats, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9436Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9436Q\"></sup>but the Arameans filled the country.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9437R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9437R\"></sup>a man of God came near and spoke to the king of Israel and said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Because the Arameans have said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9437S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9437S\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a god of <i>the</i> mountains, but He is not a god of <i>the</i> valleys,” therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9437T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9437T\"></sup>I will give all this great multitude into your hand, and you shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So they camped one over against the other seven days. And on the seventh day the battle was joined, and the sons of Israel killed <i>of</i> the Arameans 100,000 foot soldiers in one day.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But the rest fled to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9439U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9439U\"></sup>Aphek into the city, and the wall fell on 27,000 men who were left. And Ben-hadad fled and came into the city <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9439V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9439V\"></sup>into an inner chamber.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9440W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9440W\"></sup>His servants said to him, “Behold now, we have heard that the kings of the house of Israel are merciful kings, please let us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9440X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9440X\"></sup>put sackcloth on our loins and ropes on our heads, and go out to the king of Israel; perhaps he will save your life.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9441Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9441Y\"></sup>they girded sackcloth on their loins and <i>put</i> ropes on their heads, and came to the king of Israel and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9441Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9441Z\"></sup>Your servant Ben-hadad says, ‘Please let me live.’” And he said, “Is he still alive? He is my brother.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now the men took this as an omen, and quickly catching his word said, “Your brother Ben-hadad.” Then he said, “Go, bring him.” Then Ben-hadad came out to him, and he took him up into the chariot.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><i>Ben-hadad</i> said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9443AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9443AA\"></sup>The cities which my father took from your father I will restore, and you shall make streets for yourself in Damascus, as my father made in Samaria.” <i>Ahab said</i>, “And I will let you go with this covenant.” So he made a covenant with him and let him go.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Now a certain man of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9444AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9444AB\"></sup>the sons of the prophets said to another <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9444AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9444AC\"></sup>by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Please strike me.” But the man refused to strike him.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then he said to him, “Because you have not listened to the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, behold, as soon as you have departed from me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9445AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9445AD\"></sup>a lion will kill you.” And as soon as he had departed from him a lion found him and killed him.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then he found another man and said, “Please strike me.” And the man struck him, wounding him.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>So the prophet departed and waited for the king by the way, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9447AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9447AE\"></sup>disguised himself with a bandage over his eyes.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>As the king passed by, he cried to the king and said, “Your servant went out into the midst of the battle; and behold, a man turned aside and brought a man to me and said, ‘Guard this man; if for any reason he is missing, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9448AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9448AF\"></sup>then your life shall be for his life, or else you shall pay a talent of silver.’",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>While your servant was busy here and there, he was gone.” And the king of Israel said to him, “So shall your judgment be; you yourself have decided <i>it</i>.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then he hastily took the bandage away from his eyes, and the king of Israel recognized him that he was of the prophets.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>He said to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Because you have let go out of <i>your</i> hand the man whom I had devoted to destruction, therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9451AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9451AG\"></sup>your life shall go for his life, and your people for his people.’”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9452AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9452AH\"></sup>the king of Israel went to his house sullen and vexed, and came to Samaria."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Now it came about after these things that Naboth the Jezreelite had a vineyard which <i>was</i> in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9453A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9453A\"></sup>Jezreel beside the palace of Ahab king of Samaria.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Ahab spoke to Naboth, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9454B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9454B\"></sup>Give me your vineyard, that I may have it for a vegetable garden because it is close beside my house, and I will give you a better vineyard than it in its place; if you like, I will give you the price of it in money.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Naboth said to Ahab, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forbid me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9455C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9455C\"></sup>that I should give you the inheritance of my fathers.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9456D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9456D\"></sup>So Ahab came into his house sullen and vexed because of the word which Naboth the Jezreelite had spoken to him; for he said, “I will not give you the inheritance of my fathers.” And he lay down on his bed and turned away his face and ate no food.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But Jezebel his wife came to him and said to him, “How is it that your spirit is so sullen that you are not eating food?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So he said to her, “Because I spoke to Naboth the Jezreelite and said to him, ‘Give me your vineyard for money; or else, if it pleases you, I will give you a vineyard in its place.’ But he said, ‘I will not give you my vineyard.’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Jezebel his wife said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9459E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9459E\"></sup>Do you now reign over Israel? Arise, eat bread, and let your heart be joyful; I will give you the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9460F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9460F\"></sup>So she wrote letters in Ahab’s name and sealed them with his seal, and sent letters to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9460G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9460G\"></sup>the elders and to the nobles who were living with Naboth in his city.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now she wrote in the letters, saying, “Proclaim a fast and seat Naboth at the head of the people;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and seat two <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9462H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9462H\"></sup>worthless men before him, and let them testify against him, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9462I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9462I\"></sup>You cursed God and the king.’ Then take him out and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9462J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9462J\"></sup>stone him to death.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So the men of his city, the elders and the nobles who lived in his city, did as Jezebel had sent <i>word</i> to them, just as it was written in the letters which she had sent them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9464K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9464K\"></sup>proclaimed a fast and seated Naboth at the head of the people.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the two worthless men came in and sat before him; and the worthless men testified against him, even against Naboth, before the people, saying, “Naboth cursed God and the king.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9465L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9465L\"></sup>So they took him outside the city and stoned him to death with stones.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then they sent <i>word</i> to Jezebel, saying, “Naboth has been stoned and is dead.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Jezebel heard that Naboth had been stoned and was dead, Jezebel said to Ahab, “Arise, take possession of the vineyard of Naboth, the Jezreelite, which he refused to give you for money; for Naboth is not alive, but dead.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When Ahab heard that Naboth was dead, Ahab arose to go down to the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, to take possession of it.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Elijah the Tishbite, saying,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Arise, go down to meet Ahab king of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9470M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9470M\"></sup>who is in Samaria; behold, he is in the vineyard of Naboth where he has gone down to take possession of it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You shall speak to him, saying, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9471N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9471N\"></sup>Have you murdered and also taken possession?”’ And you shall speak to him, saying, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9471O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9471O\"></sup>In the place where the dogs licked up the blood of Naboth the dogs will lick up your blood, even yours.”’”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Ahab said to Elijah, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9472P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9472P\"></sup>Have you found me, O my enemy?” And he answered, “I have found <i>you</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9472Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9472Q\"></sup>because you have sold yourself to do evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Behold, I will bring evil upon you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9473R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9473R\"></sup>will utterly sweep you away, and will cut off from Ahab every male, both bond and free in Israel;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9474S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9474S\"></sup>I will make your house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9474T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9474T\"></sup>like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah, because of the provocation with which you have provoked <i>Me</i> to anger, and <i>because</i> you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9474U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9474U\"></sup>have made Israel sin.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Of Jezebel also has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoken, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9475V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9475V\"></sup>The dogs will eat Jezebel in the district of Jezreel.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9476W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9476W\"></sup>The one belonging to Ahab, who dies in the city, the dogs will eat, and the one who dies in the field the birds of heaven will eat.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9477X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9477X\"></sup>Surely there was no one like Ahab who sold himself to do evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because Jezebel his wife incited him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9478Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9478Y\"></sup>He acted very abominably in following idols, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9478Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9478Z\"></sup>according to all that the Amorites had done, whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> cast out before the sons of Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>It came about when Ahab heard these words, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9479AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9479AA\"></sup>he tore his clothes and put on sackcloth and fasted, and he lay in sackcloth and went about despondently.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Elijah the Tishbite, saying,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Do you see how Ahab has humbled himself before Me? Because he has humbled himself before Me, I will not bring the evil in his days, <i>but</i> I will bring the evil upon his house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9481AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9481AB\"></sup>in his son’s days.”"
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>Three years passed without war between Aram and Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9483A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9483A\"></sup>In the third year <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9483B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9483B\"></sup>Jehoshaphat the king of Judah came down to the king of Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now the king of Israel said to his servants, “Do you know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9484C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9484C\"></sup>Ramoth-gilead belongs to us, and we are still doing nothing to take it out of the hand of the king of Aram?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he said to Jehoshaphat, “Will you go with me to battle at Ramoth-gilead?” And Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9485D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9485D\"></sup>I am as you are, my people as your people, my horses as your horses.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Moreover, Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, “Please inquire first for the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9487E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9487E\"></sup>the king of Israel gathered the prophets together, about four hundred men, and said to them, “Shall I go against Ramoth-gilead to battle or shall I refrain?” And they said, “Go up, for the Lord will give <i>it</i> into the hand of the king.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9488F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9488F\"></sup>Jehoshaphat said, “Is there not yet a prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> here that we may inquire of him?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “There is yet one man by whom we may inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but I hate him, because he does not prophesy good concerning me, but evil. <i>He is</i> Micaiah son of Imlah.” But Jehoshaphat said, “Let not the king say so.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the king of Israel called an officer and said, “Bring quickly Micaiah son of Imlah.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah were sitting each on his throne, arrayed in <i>their</i> robes, at the threshing floor at the entrance of the gate of Samaria; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9491G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9491G\"></sup>all the prophets were prophesying before them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9492H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9492H\"></sup>horns of iron for himself and said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9492I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9492I\"></sup>With these you will gore the Arameans until they are consumed.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>All the prophets were prophesying thus, saying, “Go up to Ramoth-gilead and prosper, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give <i>it</i> into the hand of the king.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the messenger who went to summon Micaiah spoke to him saying, “Behold now, the words of the prophets are uniformly favorable to the king. Please let your word be like the word of one of them, and speak favorably.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But Micaiah said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9495J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9495J\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, what <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9495K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9495K\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says to me, that I shall speak.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When he came to the king, the king said to him, “Micaiah, shall we go to Ramoth-gilead to battle, or shall we refrain?” And he answered him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9496L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9496L\"></sup>Go up and succeed, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give <i>it</i> into the hand of the king.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the king said to him, “How many times must I adjure you to speak to me nothing but the truth in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So he said,“I saw all IsraelScattered on the mountains,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9498M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9498M\"></sup>Like sheep which have no shepherd.And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, ‘These have no master.Let each of them return to his house in peace.’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9499N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9499N\"></sup>Did I not tell you that he would not prophesy good concerning me, but evil?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Micaiah said, “Therefore, hear the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9500O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9500O\"></sup>I saw the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sitting on His throne, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9500P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9500P\"></sup>all the host of heaven standing by Him on His right and on His left.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, ‘Who will entice Ahab to go up and fall at Ramoth-gilead?’ And one said this while another said that.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then a spirit came forward and stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, ‘I will entice him.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, ‘How?’ And he said, ‘I will go out and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9503Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9503Q\"></sup>be a deceiving spirit in the mouth of all his prophets.’ Then He said, ‘You are to entice <i>him</i> and also prevail. Go and do so.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now therefore, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9504R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9504R\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has put a deceiving spirit in the mouth of all these your prophets; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has proclaimed disaster against you.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9505S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9505S\"></sup>Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah came near and struck Micaiah on the cheek and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9505T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9505T\"></sup>How did the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> pass from me to speak to you?”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Micaiah said, “Behold, you shall see on that day when you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9506U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9506U\"></sup>enter an inner room to hide yourself.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the king of Israel said, “Take Micaiah and return him to Amon the governor of the city and to Joash the king’s son;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and say, ‘Thus says the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9508V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9508V\"></sup>Put this man in prison and feed him sparingly with bread and water until I return safely.”’”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Micaiah said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9509W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9509W\"></sup>If you indeed return safely the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not spoken by me.” And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9509X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9509X\"></sup>Listen, all you people.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9510Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9510Y\"></sup>the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah went up against Ramoth-gilead.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9511Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9511Z\"></sup>I will disguise myself and go into the battle, but you put on your robes.” So the king of Israel disguised himself and went into the battle.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9512AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9512AA\"></sup>the king of Aram had commanded the thirty-two captains of his chariots, saying, “Do not fight with small or great, but with the king of Israel alone.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So when the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat, they said, “Surely it is the king of Israel,” and they turned aside to fight against him, and Jehoshaphat cried out.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When the captains of the chariots saw that it was not the king of Israel, they turned back from pursuing him.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now a certain man drew his bow at random and struck the king of Israel in a joint of the armor. So he said to the driver of his chariot, “Turn around and take me out of the fight; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9515AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9515AB\"></sup>for I am severely wounded.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The battle raged that day, and the king was propped up in his chariot in front of the Arameans, and died at evening, and the blood from the wound ran into the bottom of the chariot.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9517AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9517AC\"></sup>Then a cry passed throughout the army close to sunset, saying, “Every man to his city and every man to his country.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So the king died and was brought to Samaria, and they buried the king in Samaria.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>They washed the chariot by the pool of Samaria, and the dogs licked up his blood (now the harlots bathed themselves <i>there</i>), <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9519AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9519AD\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which He spoke.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Ahab and all that he did and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9520AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9520AE\"></sup>the ivory house which he built and all the cities which he built, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>So Ahab slept with his fathers, and Ahaziah his son became king in his place.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9522AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9522AF\"></sup>Now Jehoshaphat the son of Asa became king over Judah in the fourth year of Ahab king of Israel.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Jehoshaphat was thirty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned twenty-five years in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name was Azubah the daughter of Shilhi.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9524AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9524AG\"></sup>He walked in all the way of Asa his father; he did not turn aside from it, doing right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9524AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9524AH\"></sup>However, the high places were not taken away; the people still sacrificed and burnt incense on the high places.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9525AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9525AI\"></sup>Jehoshaphat also made peace with the king of Israel.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, and his might which he showed and how he warred, are they not written <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9526AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9526AJ\"></sup>in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>The remnant of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9527AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9527AK\"></sup>the sodomites who remained in the days of his father Asa, he expelled from the land.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9528AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9528AL\"></sup>there was no king in Edom; a deputy was king.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Jehoshaphat made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9529AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9529AM\"></sup>ships of Tarshish to go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9529AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9529AN\"></sup>Ophir for gold, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9529AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9529AO\"></sup>they did not go for the ships were broken at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9529AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9529AP\"></sup>Ezion-geber.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Then Ahaziah the son of Ahab said to Jehoshaphat, “Let my servants go with your servants in the ships.” But Jehoshaphat was not willing.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9531AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9531AQ\"></sup>And Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the city of his father David, and Jehoram his son became king in his place.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Ahaziah the son of Ahab <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9532AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9532AR\"></sup>became king over Israel in Samaria in the seventeenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and he reigned two years over Israel.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9533AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9533AS\"></sup>walked in the way of his father and in the way of his mother and in the way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who caused Israel to sin.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9534AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9534AT\"></sup>So he served Baal and worshiped him and provoked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel to anger, according to all that his father had done."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;